subject: Sanmina SCI_SS-DL-00391_42Q_BRM Issue
description_text:
Hi KY team
  The duplicate barcode error happens when machine having paste inspection error and material has run out.
  This is dual lane SPI, both lanes turn on BRM, use client ID 022, Lane 1 uses workstation 1, lane 2 uses workstation 2.
  If no inspection error or material has run out error, the machine can run as normal.
  Please investigate what causes this error and provide a solution soonest posible.
  Attached the BRM logs file and error msg

subject: SPI and AOI freezing when the Ksmart server gets frozen when it gets to 100% of the processor
description_text: Our client Jabil had a problem with SPI and AOI crashing during production. We identified that the problem occurred when KSMART was using 100% CPU. After restarting KSMART, the CPU dropped to 20% and the machines started working normally again, but the same symptom occurred again in less than 30 minutes.     After a few tests we noticed that the problem occurs when we open the DASHBOARD page,  If we restart and do not open the dashboard page, CPU usage remains low,   If we start the DASHBOARD page, the CPU usage goes up until the machines crash,     Below is the version of Ksmart and GUI:  Ksmart Version: Ver 2.2.0.0.T06  AP-SL-01350: 2.7.4.3_H01(124024)  AP-SL-01408: 2.7.4.3_H01(130276)  AP-SL-01233: 2.7.4.3_H01(124024)  AP-SL-02128: 2.7.4.3_H01(130276)  AP-SL-01673: 2.7.4.3_H01(130276)  AP-SL-01636: 2.7.4.3_H01(130276)     Could you help us with this problem?  CPU with 100%       CPU After restart:       CPU when open DASHBOARD page:

subject: Cambio de buffer en AOI linea 3
description_text:
Buen día,

En la linea 3 anteriormente teniamos un buffer en donde se almacenaban las piezas despues de la inspeccion de AOI y estas se tenian que escanear por parte del operador en la repair station para poder ver las fallas de la AOI,

actualmente instalamos un buffer diferente y queremos que como en las demas lineas haga match el buffer con la repair, que no haya necesidad de escanear las piezas despues de la inspeccion si no que se almacenen en el buffer y se juzguen directamente desde la repair station.

hay algun metodo para dar de alta el equipo nuevo en la maquina AOI y que configuraciones se requieren hacer ?

gracias por su atencion.

[cid:fe6b7088-e22c-4b9c-8942-e872d589f8ca]

subject: Customer Ericsson Tallinn: Ksmart job loading issues and Ksmart webgui pages doesn't open
description_text: Hi,  Description: Ericsson Tallinn reports that suddenly they started to receive job loading errorMsg's and job loading menu takes a long time to open. Eventually, job loading menu did not open at all and login to AoiGui stopped working, until after Ksmart restart.   Actions/Conditions: - When job loading issues occured, customer restarted Ksmart from webgui.   This helped a couple of times, but then server/webgui froze completly. - A hard reset was done and Ksmart started working again.  - Issue was seen in several machines. - Ksmart-->Settings-->ServerSettings page doesn't open, so webmanager log cannot be downloaded (today).     Questions: 1. Can KYE connect and have a look? (waiting for TV info) 2. I've sent putty & HeidiSQL to customer and asked them to put it on machine desktop.      Any other sw's needed?  Best regards  Anders

subject: Customer NOKIA: CFX - NOKIA wants to install ASM RSF client to all KohYoung machines
description_text: Hi,  Background: This is one of many tickets, related to activation of CFX at NOKIA in w51 2023-12-21.            Description: Nokia wants to install ASM RSF client to all KohYoung machines, to utilize ASM Remote Smart Factory and customer cockpit sw. ASM RSF: https://smt.asmpt.com/en/news-center/news/asm-remote-smart-factory/ Video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dh37FVZOPCQ  ASM RSF client is using port 7778 TCP\SSL for communication.  Questions: 1. Does KY know if ASM RSF client can be installed to KohYoung machines, without any risk of KY sw functionality? 2. Does KY know of any customer that is currently using ASM RSF client in KohYoung machines?    Best regards  Anders

subject: SPI down
description_text:
Hi KY team,

We currently have an SPI (SS-SL-08282) that will not boot. It began with the PC freezing then it would not get past the POST and would stay showing a blinking underscore “_”. I ran the different startup repair options on the windows CD and was able to get it to start loading Windows but it now gives a Blue Screen of Death (see attached). This system has a RAID module and I’ve tried booting with each individual disks to no avail. I tested the Windows drives on another PC and was able to access its files without problems which makes me believe the problem is not related to Hard drives. I installed 2 new drives and restored a Acronis backup image (from last year) but it gives the same BSOD upon boot. Any advice?

The PC is an OptiPlex 5820 with 128gb RAM and a 4TB (KSMART LINK) hard drive attached.

Thanks in advance!
Kevin M. Ramos Cortés | Manufacturing Engineer - PRE
COLLINS AEROSPACE
Felicia Industrial Park, Carr.538 KM 0.7 Street B Lot 14, Call Box 2805, Santa Isabel, P.R. 00757
Tel: +1 787-845-4343

subject: Lubrication of ball screws and linear guides
description_text: Hello KY team,     Our Flex Jaguariúna customer reported some problems when he went to perform preventive maintenance on the Zenith UHS.            The first point is the ball screw. The ball screw has a hole (image below), this hole does not allow the grease to come out at the back of the ball screw, the grease ends up coming out on the side                   The second point mentioned by them is the linear guide. The grease nipple of the linear guide is very close to the guide, making it impossible to fit the flexible grease fitting onto the grease nipple.            Have only 6mm between the grease nipple and the linear guide. Have any grease gun especific for this machine??        If you need more information, contact us!     Thank you!  Lucas Fernandes

subject: Koh Young AOIs \ Aegis FactoryLogix CFX issue  #58558230
description_text:
Hi KY Support,
I need someone to help me find where the Koh Young AOIs get the “RelevantSurface” information which it passes to our Aegis FactoryLogix software via the CFX interface as part of the Recipeactivated message (See CFX Log example below). I have an active support case with Aegis software (CAS-77396-C5H2P7) and we have determined the Relevantsurface information always appears as “SecondarySurface” and never appears to change to “PrimarySurface “ as we would expect it to when we load a recipe for the TOP side of a PCBA. This occurs at all KY AOI machines. Aegis did make a code change to start using the CFX “RelevantSurface” in a recent release of their application.

[cid:image001.png@01D9BA5E.DD5E7EB0]

DONNIE SMITH

subject: SPI Light Setting Issue
description_text: Good Morning Koh Young,     we have been experiencing an issue where in some jobs the "Projector Lights" setting in both "Global" and "Per Job" are set to off.  Only one can be selected, and after applying, saving and reopening settings they are turned off again.  This is causing issues with Bare Board Training, but not for every job we have run.  Sometimes it is Jobs for both sides, sometimes for just on side, and on other Jobs it works as intended for both sides of other assemblies.     Matt Smith

subject: AOI Review Station Main - Skin 설정 관련 문의 件
description_text:
안녕하세요 프러스전자 김선남 대리입니다.


자사에서 사용중인 3D AOI Review Station Main - Skin 설정 관련

문제가 있어 확인 요청 드립니다.

현재 Review Setup에서 Reveiw - Basic TAB의 Main - Skin 설정을

Review - Review로 사용 중인데 해당 옵션으로 설정 시 정상 이미지가

자재 1Point 기준이 아닌 PCB 전체로 출력이 되어 검사 판정에 어려움이 있습니다.

Review - CRDType3로 설정할 경우에는 정상 이미지가 자재 기준으로 출력이 되는 것을 확인 했으나

해당 옵션 사용 시에는 PCB 최종 판정 버튼이 UI에 표시되지 않습니다.

각 옵션 설정 시 Review Station 화면 첨부 파일 확인 요청 드리며

제가 말씀드린 두 가지 기능을 모두 충족할 다른 설정이 있는지 확인 부탁 드립니다.

Review Station Ver. : 2.6.0.2


감사합니다.

subject: AOI LEAD 중첩 CONNECTOR 검사 가능 여부 문의 件
description_text: 안녕하세요? 디에이치라이팅 김진현 매니저입니다.     표제와 같이 형상과 리드 배열이 특이한 커넥터를 검사해야하는데 해당 커넥터 제작 전      문제되는 부분을 미리 체크하고자 아래 내용 문의 드리오니 의견 부탁 드립니다.     주요 문의사항  1. 커넥터 3D형상오류  > 높이 약 11mm 커넥터이며 윗면 형상이 불규칙함, 정상적으로 3D 형상 구현 가능한지?      2. 리드 간 피치 협소로 인한 리드 인식 가능여부 및 가성불량 우려  > AOI 인식가능한 피치가 최소 몇 mm가 필요한지? 의견부탁드립니다.     3. 리드 끝 위치가 사진과 같이 상이함  > 해당과 같은 배열의 리드 검사 시 특이사항이 있다면 의견부탁드립니다.      4. 리드팁이 돌출되어있지 않은데 솔더 필렛 검사가 가능한지?  > 사진 리드 끝단을 보시면 ⊃ 형상으로 리드팁 부위가 관통되어 있습니다.  > 해당 부위에 필렛이 형성될 시 검출 가능한지 의견 부탁드립니다.  > 만약 불가하다면 리드 ⊃ 형상 위쪽으로 리드를 절삭할 예정인데 최소 몇mm정도의 팁이 필요할지 의견 부탁드립니다. (사진2 참조)        [사진1]       [사진2]          바쁘시겠지만 의견 부탁 드립니다.     이상입니다.

subject: AOI 프로그램 관련 문의 드립니다.
description_text: 안녕하세요 광주 월드플러스전자 김정일 입니다.     AOI 프로그램 관련 하여 문의 드립니다.     1. A 라는 프로그램을 생성하여 네트워크가 연결되지 않은 오프라인 신규 장비에서 바로 사용할수있는 방법이 있나요     2. 신규장비는 패키지정보가 아무것도 없습니다.     3. 현재 사용중이 장비의 패키지를 신규장비에 복사하는 방법이 있나요??

subject: [Yokote Seiko]KSMART 서버의 특정로그(ksmart-rotate-partition.log)가 계속 축적되는 문제 확인 지원 요청
description_text: 배경 및 내용  Yokote 고객사에서 SPC@KSMART 기능을 사용한 이후로, HDD사용이 Full로 차는 현상이 발생하여, SPC@KSMART기능을 OFF한 이후, 연말의 휴지기간에 KSMART서버의 버전업 및 불필요한 데이터삭제를 위해서 원격 접속을 진행하였습니다.  Putty를 이용하여, 각 폴더의 사용 용량의 비율을 Tracking한 결과, ksmart-rotate-partition.log 파일이 2.5TB를 차지하면서 3.5TB의 HDD의 대부분을 사용하는 것이 확인이 되었습니다.  원격으로 해당 로그를 삭제하였으나, 신규로 파일 생성 및 로그가 축적이 되는 상황이 확인이 되었습니다. (모니터링 결과로는 1시간에 약 400MB씩 쌓이고 있습니다.)  해당 로그의 내용을 확인을 하면, PARTITION작성에 문제가 있는 것으로 보이나, 내용의 확인 지원이 필요합니다.       관련하여, 축적되는 로그 파일 및 KSMART Log파일을 하기의 링크로 업데이트 전달 드립니다.  20231228 Yokote Seiko KSMART LOG      원격으로 KSMSART 웹매니저 버전을 "ksmart_2.2.0.3(Rev2).pat"으로 업데이트를 하여도 상기의 상황은 개선이 되지 않았습니다.  여타 다른 특이사항은, CPU의 사용율이 100%를 계속 유지하는 점, 서버 모델 타입이 N/A로 표시가 되는 점등이 특이한 좀으로 캐치가 되었습니다.  담당 기술 엔지니어의 이력 확인으로는, KSMART설치 시에 트러블 대응으로 RnD의 원격지원이 최초에 있던 상황까지는 체크 되었습니다.     해당 고객사는 원격 확인 지원이 가능하기에 1월8일 이후의 일정으로 KYHQ 및 RnD의 원격 일정의 조율이 되면, 담당 영업/기술을 통해서 고객과 커뮤니케이션 하도록 하겠습니다.

subject: Issue with AOI L13
description_text:
¡Qué tal team, buenos días!

De su apoyo para poder diagnosticar con el siguiente problema que nos estamos encontrando en un equipo de AOI, este por alguna razón deja de reportar información al KSmart por lo que tenemos que restablecer al momento con el reinicio de la aplicación de review y AOIGUI. La situación es que el producto que corre es muy critico y por ninguna razón se puede detener esta línea.

[cid:image002.png@01DA3FC1.ED510980]

1 - ¿Posible causa raíz de que se esté generando más frecuente este issue?
2 - ¿Existe alguna configuración que pueda mitigar este issue?
3 - ¿Existe un indicador o algún stop de línea cuando esto ocurra?
4 - ¿Por qué la información se pierde y no se restablece cuando el equipo se vuelve a conectar con KSmart?
5 - ¿Existe alguna copia de seguridad que nos ayude a recuperar esta información?

Regards!

Vicente A. De la Cruz
Test Tech

subject: Ksmart no refleja status de piezas clasificadas en Review Station
description_text:
Buena tarde Equipo de Koh Young

Requiero de su soporte con un equipo de AOI ya que no se refleja el status de piezas ya clasificadas en Review Station.

El equipo esta conectado al servidor Ksmart, cuando las piezas fallan en AOI en el servidor se quedan en espera de ser clasificadas (en color amarillo) el detalle es que después de ser clasificadas en la Review el status sigue siendo el mismo en el servidor, no se ve reflejado que ya fue clasificada.

To: Ivan Aduna <ivan.aduna@kohyoung.com>
Cc: Tim Mccarthey <Tim.Mccarthey@plexus.com>
Subject: Trial of CFX data from Koh Young machines

Hi Ivan,
I am looking to do some trials with some realtime data dashboards and analytics software at our Plexus Kelso site with data harvested from AOI, AXI and Test equipment.
We are setting up a Message Broker that can process Connected Factory Exchange (CFX) data streams.

I'd like to explore the possibility to have the 2x Koh Young machines (and their associated Review stations) at Kelso setup to output their inspection results data in CFX format to the Message Broker.
I understand there is a CFX plugin available. Would it be possible modify the KBR files to enable a CFX data stream on a trial basis? How would we go about this?
Thanks,
Ian.

subject: Prueba en terminales no detectada
description_text:
Buenas tardes

El día de hoy se tuvo el siguiente evento, al inspeccionar el componente que se muestra en la siguiente imagen, solo muestra las pruebas del body y omite las de las terminales. Esto a pesar de tener habilitada la prueba de soldadura correspondiente a este componente, como se muestra en la imagen.

En realidad las pruebas en terminales no se estaban detectando, ya que al pasar una pieza con falla en terminales no detectaba la falla.

Esto ocurrió en dos modelos diferentes el día de hoy.

Al cerrar el programa y la aplicación y volver a cargar el programa, las pruebas en terminales ya se mostraban al inspeccionar el componente.

Esto se presenta en la maquina ALU-SL-00067.

Solicitamos su apoyo para el problema ocurrido.

[cid:e3a21010-aa1e-46c8-be34-6f5ac48696c2]

Agradezco y quedo atenta a sus comentarios. Muchas gracias.

Saludos cordiales, Mit freundlichen Grüssen, Best Regards

Liliana Lopez

subject: need support to implement a barcode mismatch detection.
description_text:
Hello KY team,

This is Ignacio from Salcomp Tx.
We are not able to contact you from our company e-mail yet, so I am using my personal one.
We need your support to implement a pockayoke on KY machines.
Once in a while we have an issue with our printed barcodes not matching the printed serial numbers. When this happens, hundreds of boards are sent to scrapp due to the discrepancies, so we want to implement an early detection. The machine will need to read the barcode and the printed serial number, then compare them and if they don't match, the machine should shoot an error and stop operation.
take a look on the next sample, when we read the barcode the number on it is the 761 instead of the 759
[image.png]
[image.png]
Please let me know if it is possible to make such improvements and how we can make it possible.

Best regards

subject: SPI running slow.
description_text:
Good morning,
We are having an issue with one of our SPIs (SN: ss-sl-00258) there is a delay that occurs between a board entering and the fiducial inspection beginning and another delay between the final fiducial inspection and the board inspection beginning. These delays are extending the overall inspection time by 20-40 seconds per board and are slowing the pace of the line.

I would like to schedule a support session for mid-day today 12:00 central time. Please let me know if you can accommodate.

subject: [NSN_Chennai]_Kohyoung AOI_Long board option enable issue in RIGHT to LEFT configuration machines
description_text:
Dear team,     Hi,
  In NOKIA ,  we enabled long board option in AOI.
     Long board option working fine in Left to right (L->R) machine configuration. We didn't face any error.
     In Right to left (R->L) machine configuration, while board entering time step2 board stopper was close. Due to board not go up to inspection area and shows board not arrive error .
  So we observed in Right to left configuration machine  , step 1 & 2 board stop sensors and hard stop cylinders working as left to right machine only. For Time being we interchanged the step 1 & 2  board stop sensor power connections and hard stop cylinder hose connection also. After that board inspection was ok.
  If we want to disable long board option  , In L->R config machine , need to disable long board option in winmcs only .  But in R->L configuration machine , long board option need to disable in Winmcs as well as need to interchange  step 1 & 2  hardware connection also.(Board stop sensor power connection & cylinder hose connection)  Customer don't want to interchange hardware connections to disable long board option in R->L configuration machine.   Need to support to close the issue.     Regards  Sethu

 MAE Protocol

subject: AW: BBT strange behavior
description_text:
Dear Amit,

as you suggested we checked if the behavior is different by using of Auto or normal by Vendor to use. This has no effect.
[cid:image001.png@01D8651A.125ADF50]

After that we recreated the job file.
We have the same behavior. BBT Data will take effect after restarting of the software.
As you can see (PP1SMT5_vorher.jpg) after automatic change over (load) many insufficient data, after restarting of the software (PP1SMT5_nachher.jpg) everything is fine.

Any new ideas what can we do? To catch the product during run and make a remote session is difficult….



Mit freundlichen Grüßen / Best regards

Attila Nagy
SzP/MST4

Tel. +49 5341 28-7480 | Mobil +49 173 6224471
​
Von: Nagy Attila (SzP/MST4)
Gesendet: Mittwoch, 30. März 2022 09:54
An: Europe Support <kye_help@kohyoung.com>
Cc: Amit Kumar <amit.kumar@kohyoung.com>
Betreff: BBT strange behavior

Dear Amit,

We are facing in the last time some issues regarding BBT. Affected is one machine aSPIre3 (SP-SL-00272).

As you can see in the attached screenshot, after restarting of the software the inspection was running more smoothly (histogram is showing a normal behavior, more narrow), we didn’t have the failure any more.

Some hour before of this restart we had the issue that some pads failed with insufficient volume. BBT was performed and the failure fixed (no insufficient failure any more). After this product ran in the line another product. Some times later comes the same product again and the problem with the insufficient volume occurred again. After restarting the software (as described before) the failure disappeared. It seems that the BBT data was not considered, only after restarting the software (normal changeover was not enough). This phenomena we observe in this machine for several products.
I hope I described the issue in a way that you can understand what I mean.

Do you have any idea, what can be the root cause for that? Which data do you need to investigate?
Thank you for your support.

Mit freundlichen Grüßen / Best regards

Attila Nagy

subject: Customer Nokia: WorkOut & WorkSlow sensors has no power supply (AP-SX-00088)
description_text:
Hi,  Description: Nokia reports that suddenly WorkOut X02 & WorkSlow X01 sensors has no power supply. Everything else in machine seems to be working.     Actions: - Customer confirmed that both sensors are good and working, if they have power supply. - Electrical diagram doesn't match std C-platform doc in FTP (unless I'm mistaken, see attached doc). - When customer compares machine to other machines (e.g. AP-SX-0070) , X02 & X01 connector connected in Gnet D I/O board has 3 wires. - AP-SX-00088 only has 2 wires in X02 & X01 connectors, while AP-SX-00070 has 3 wires. - PS2 is DC24V   Customer was able to use X07-connector from the bensor connector block, at rail1 to find a temporary solution (see below).  AP-SX-00088 WorkOut & WorkSlow issue workAround  1. WorkOut & WorkSlow sensors not working-->No power
  2. In the connector-block: Moved X02-Sensor connector --> to X07 (not used)
  3. In Gnet D I/O board: Disconnect X02 connector
  4. In Gnet D I/O board: Connect X07-cable connector in Gnet D I/O connector
     (WorkOut is using the X07-cable (KYES-330033-01) from Sensor connector block --> Gnet D I/O)
  5. WorkSlow not connected in Gnet (seems to work, but needs to be fixed)
     (Only 2 wires connected in Gnet D I/O X01 connector, 3rd wire goes to YE0 OUT14 cable. Where does it end up?)
 6. WorkSlow sensor currently not used, since machine operation is working without.  ​​​​​​                    Temporary fixed, by using cable KYES-330033-01 and connect it to Gnet D I/O X02-connector:
        Gnet D I/O board:
        YE0 OUT14 connector (doesn't exist in std C-platform electrical diagram):
        Files:  - Comparing images between AP-SX-00088 & AP-SX-00070, showing 3 vs 2 wires in Gnet D I/O board connectors.  https://we.tl/t-MEmbw2RU2T     Questions: 1. Can KYE send correct electrical diagram for AP-SX-00088? 2. Why is wiring different in Gnet D I/O board connector X02 & X01 --> 3 vs 2 wires in connector in Gnet D I/O board) between AP-SX-00088 & AP-SX-00070? 3. Reference/label YE0 OUT14 (as seen in images) doesn't exist in electrical diagram (do I have the wrong diagram, attached)? 4. Where does YE0 OUT14 go, so that customer can check the connection? 5. Is it +DC24V, signal or ground wire, that is connected to YE0 OUT14? 6. What parts might need replacement?     Best regards Anders

subject: Jabil Viet Nam_Ksmart Can not show image false call or NG
description_text: Hi KY team,     Other issue occurred in workcell ING in Jabil VN.  Last time they have 5 lines use KY machine windows 7, AOI GUI ver 2.7.4.1 H03 and Ksmart ver 2.2.0.0 T06 then they configured used Agent method without KsmartBase. Then in Ksmart Web can show image false call / NG for 2D,3D image and information.     But after used AOIGUI ver 2.7.5.0 H02 or higher and upgrade Ksmart Web to ver 2.2.0.1 or higher.  Customer can not collect the  info, image 2D,3D for result false call / NG .     Screen waiting long time and can't show any thing.     But they have a some line used windows 10 then we apply to Ksmart@Client then can see image 2D,3D false call or NG     For these windows 7 for 5 AOI stations KY, once we exchange from KSA to Ksmart@Client. (tried almost KsmartClient version)  - Almost machine happened issue cycle time increase so much from 12s to 45s on many job file . Trying many method but cycle time inspection still high, finally change back then run as normal  - Sometimes after exchange then AOI GUI crash always. once change back then normal     ALso we tried installed KSmartBase and setting but still no see image.     Can you help to check with your R&D about method suitable can show 2D,3D image , information for False call / NG result on Ksmart when use AOIGUI ver 2.7.5.0 or higher, and Ksmart Web 2.2.0.1 or higher?     Now we already upgrade Ksmart 2.2.0.1 XX and old data lost then can not come back lower version.      Lets me know if you have any update.  Thanks

description_text: Hello dear KY team,     We had an issue at Draexlmaier Timisoare with an SPI equipment SN: SS-SL-03472, after a short power down, at job file  190055731-024 Top and Bottom.  The description of the issue is:  Inspection doesn't start at job file 190055731-024 and sometime the WinMCS is closing.  We put a backup from 04.2023, reinstall the GUI, KYCal, WinMCS. I reinstalled also partition S, teach again the fiducial and Bare code, FOV Optimization but the same. The inspection doesn't start after the  reading of fiducial and bare code, but no error appear, and also sometime the WinMCS turned of by himself .     After this we tried with other job and works without the issue.  I want to specify that after I tried with the job  190055731-024 copied from this equipment on SPI from the neighbor line and there we reteach the fiducial and work's without problem.  On the following link you will find the log files, report and Job with the issue from the equipment. The issue appear at around 2AM  https://we.tl/t-oSi2xuZUdr   Can you please advice us? subject: ***URGENT*** [AOIGUI] GUI not able to save data to KYResult_xxxxxx.TB_AOIDefect table after upgrading to v2.8 - Fideltronik, AP2-SSL-00024
description_text:
Dear KYE Support,

We're here at Fideltronik again trying to upgrade their Zenith 2 machines to AOIGUI v2.8. First problem I encountered is that after inspection is done and results are saved to DB, I am unable to classify defects on Review s/w because it doesn't load the inspection result properly. Please look at the attached image compilation (problems.png).

As you can see I have tried 4 different Review s/w versions but none of them worked. After digging into the problem, I noticed that the TB_AOIDefect table in KY_Result database doesn't contain any info about my inspected PCB:
[cid:image007.jpg@01DA42E8.499AD260]

Here's the info about this PCB in TB_AOIPCB table of KY_AOI database:
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, oprogramowanie  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]

And in TB_AOIDefectDetail in KY_Result database:
[Obraz zawierający tekst, elektronika, zrzut ekranu, oprogramowanie  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]

Only that TB_AOIDefect doesn't contain any results and I guess that's why Review s/w can't load the inspection result properly.

Anyways, this is what I found in AOIGUI logs:

[2024-01-09 09:28:49] BulkInsert Begins
[2024-01-09 09:28:49] Total Result Count : 24, Result Type : Defect
[2024-01-09 09:28:49] CADOCommand Error
                Code = 80040e21
                Code meaning = IDispatch error #3105
                Source = (null)
                Description = (null)

[2024-01-09 09:28:49] BulkInsert failed (Result Type : 0, Col Error : NO, Row Error : NO)

Googling that didn't really help. I tried 2 different revisions of v2.8 software:

  *   2.8.0.2-1-g3cac1f2e3c3
  *   2.8.1.1-25-gc8c36009703(Release)

Both do the same thing. When restoring to the previously used v2.7.5 everything works well.

Please advise.

PS: Link to CheckupTool logs and the complete KYLOG folder is here: https://we.tl/t-E54EC4gzQM

Pozdrawiam/Best regards

---

Daniel Kotwicki
Service Engineer

subject: Need help on a few issues
description_text:

It has been awhile. How is the team doing?
We need your help on a few items as I have been away for a while and I don't quite remember all the settings, tricks and tips, so I appreciate any help:
It's a long list but can you help us of these 3 issues first?

-        Whole board image for all board tested: I remember there is a way to capture and save the whole board image for every board that is tested at the AOI. Can you please provide the steps for enabling this again?

Thanks!

Danny

subject: Trigger a escanner cognex
description_text:
Buenas tardes

Podrían apoyarnos por favor con una duda sobre una configuración.

Tratamos de realizar el trigger de un scanner Cognex mediante el mensaje que viene en el AOICONFIG LON/LOF por el puerto serial.

Cuando llega la pieza al scanner no realiza el trigger, sin embargo cuando hacemos el trigger desde la aplicación del scanner si lo hace.

El scanner es el modelo DM150, ya configuramos en el scanner que el trigger ON/OFF lo haga con los msj LON/LOFF.

Tambien en AOIconfig pusimos el modo pre conveyor stopper(default)

Tendrán algun manual para configurar la lectura de barcode en AOI con ese método de comunicación?

El serial de la maquina es AP-SL-00066

Gracias de antemano!
Saludos y Feliz Año Nuevo!

subject: [전유산업] GUI 2.8.1.1  WFMI 기능 활성화 시 간헐적 3D 복원 불가 증상 확인 요청
description_text: 수신: AOI Vsion Front 담당자님     안녕하세요 국내TS팀 박종현 사원입니다.     2.8.1.1 버젼 적용 이후 WFMI 기능 활성화 시 간헐적으로 부품 3D 오복원 되는 증상으로 인하여 원인 분석을 요청드립니다.      현재 10대 설비 적용을 한 상태이며 초기 이슈 발생 설비의 경우 장비 Calibration 재 진행 이후 정상 상태로 돌아왔으며 추가 한대 설비에서 동일한 증상이 발생했습니다.     버젼이 확산 되어 있는 다른 설비에서도 동일 증상 발생을 우려하고 있는 상황으로 고객사로부터 긴급으로 원인 분석 및 조치 방법을 요청 받은 상태입니다.     많이 바쁘시겠지만 확인 부탁 드리겠습니다.      추가로 필요한 파일을 알려주시면 추가 전송하겠습니다.     Issue 증상   Version 업그레이드 이후 정상 가동 중 베이스 올라옴, 부품 3D 꺼짐 증상 발생, 초기 발생 이후 간헐적 발생 중  동일 컴퍼넌트에서 발생하는 것이 아닌 해당 패키지에서 발생  WFMI 비활성화 시 아래 증상 미발생         첨부파일   1. WFMI 기능 활성화 시 간헐적 3D 오복원 발생

description_text: Hi KY Team,      KSMART Version:- 2.2.0.1_H02-T04     Customer has purchased KSMART-SPC.  They want view the Yield Status for one month or one Week.      Once they select the Time Period for one month. In that particular period they can select only any 4-Jobs.      For Example in one month if they produced 30-Jobs. They want to view only 4-Jobs. But customer wants to view the over all view for 30 Jobs in the particular period,      But in KSMART 1.3 version we can able view select all the jobs also they can able to view the Yield for one month.      Please provide us the solution for the above issue. Also please find attached Video reference.       Regards     karthikeyan,S

subject: AL-SL-00822-KSMART ARRAY BARCODE DATA IS NOT UPDATING
description_text: HI KY Team,      In SGS Bangalore. In  KSMART SPC if we search for array barcode to find the PCB result. The Data is not showing.      If we search the Master Barcode(Machine first reading barcode). we are getting the PCB result. Inside the PCB result we are getting the Array Barcode details list.      But customer wants to search the result by using the array barcode.      We request you to provide us the solution, as soon as possible. Please find attached refence video.      Regards     Karthikeyan.S

subject: Triangular Fiducials Matching with Offset [Tesat Spacecom; AP2-SSL-00019]
description_text:
Dear KYE,   our Customer Tesat is using Triangular Fiducials with most of their Products.
  Unfortunately these are Matching with an Offset all the time (see Screenshot) we tried different AOI-GUI Versions, but it only became worse. On SPI on the other Hand the Fiducials are matching without any issues.     We tried several ROI Sizes, Triangle Black, Triangle White, Unknown, ...   But there was an offset all the Time.  Parameter Auto Tuning wasn´t working either.          Customer is using:
  AOIGUI Ver: 2.7.4.3_H02
  Vision Ver: 1.0.0.1.133612(Release)
  KY-CAL Ver: 2.1.0.0 
  MCS: 800.00.6
  KYI: 1.1.13.0     Find Jobfile and AOI-Folder at: https://hidrive.ionos.com/share/5004.e4l0r     Thank you for your Support!  Best regards   Natalie

subject: [Review Station] ROI and arrows are partially displayed on neighboring component
description_text:
Hi guys,     CM Elektronik has the problem that the ROI or the arrows are sometimes displayed in the wrong position at the review station. This has occurred since the update to version 5787. 
  What we did:  We have already checked if the decimal separator is set to dot. -> Dot is selected  - checked whether a special character is stored for the component.  - checked with latest released Review version (5826)  - config.ini was created completely new with basic settings -> same issue     Details:  - You can see in the screenshot, the CRD U6 is selected  - U6 is the component, which is displayed in center  - The arrows and Component shape is displayed on U5       Please find attached logs from Review Station     Regards  Markus

subject: AOI: Data collection of fiducials?
description_text: Hi.     Sometimes there are problems with locating fiducials in production (different PWB manufacturer or something) even if they visually look OK.   Also sometimes the component inspections may be slightly misaligned or way out.  When the fiducial inspection fails the PWB is not inspected. So I assume for some reason the fiducial "is found" because the board is inspected.     Yesterday I was just testing barcode reading and I had the same job loaded for both sides of the board. I assumed the fiducials will fail when the wrong side is up - but how wrong was I, the both "fiducials" passed 90%!     Is there a setting I could turn on that - if not collects also images but at least the quality (percent) of each fiducial (with barcode of the board included)?  The other thing is the board behaviour after oven when the board is hot/warm when AOI inspection is started and while inspecting, the board cools down. Can we collect data of the machine coordinates of the fiducials when inspection started and re-inspect the fiduals (with data collection) again after inspection is done?  Maybe the slight misalignments are because the board behaves when cooling down...     I have also tried the automatic Fiducial Setting feature but I am not very convinced ...     Regards,        -Tatu-

subject: [PJ전자] KSMART Client Log 용량으로 인한 개선 요청
description_text: 과장님 안녕하세요, 고영테크놀러지 헬프데스크입니다     금일 유선으로 말씀드린바와 같이 KSMART Client Log 자동 삭제 방법에 대한 Guide 전달드리오니  하기 내용 확인하시고 문제설비에 적용후 결과 회신 부탁드리겠습니다      오래된 로그파일 삭제 방법  KSMART Client Console에 접속하고 우측 상단 로그인 화면에서 kyadmin / 21077421! 로 로그인한다.  Config 메뉴를 클릭한다  Config Detail 탭에서 Search를 log로 입력하고 검색한다  Log.MaxArchiveFiles이 검색됨을 확인하고, 이 값을  5로 변경하고, 우측의 Apply 버튼을 클릭한다  디폴트는 30인데, 5일정도 로그만 남기고 삭제한다는 의미    화면을 리프레쉬하고, Log.MaxArchiveFiles이 5로 변경이 되었는지 확인한다  윈도우 트레이 아이콘에서 KSMART Client를 재시작 한다.(Service Control>Station>Restart)  Machine 메뉴에서 장비가 다시 등록됨을 확인한다.(등록된 날짜로 확인 혹은 토스트 메시지로 확인)  로그파일 경로에 오래된 파일이 삭제됨을 확인한다.(C:\KohYoung\KsmartClient\Stream\Log, C:\KohYoung\KsmartClient\Stream\Archive)        이상입니다

subject: RE: Re:Re:버블 가성불량 개선 요청의 件.
description_text:
정종백 부장님 안녕하세요 고영 이진욱 입니다.

1차로 보내주신 버블 가성불량 케이스에 대한 자재에 대해 시뮬레이션 데이터 학습을 요청 및 진행해 볼 계획입니다. 이에 대한 내용을 전달 드립니다.

현재 두가지 문제가 있는데요


  1.  가성불량 케이스로만 신규버블엔진 학습을 진행 해 본 케이스가 없음

  *   보통은 실제 불량 케이스를 기준으로 학습합니다. 그래서 유관부서의 피드백을 통해 개발가능여부를 1차 검토 예정입니다.
  *   상기의 케이스로만 개발 불가 시에는 차후 실제 불량 케이스들을 모아서 2차 학습을 진행 해야 합니다.


  1.  본사 설비에서는 여러 개의 버블을 하나의 버블로 디텍되는 사례가 발견되지 않음

  *   해당 사례의 기준으로 시뮬레이션 데이터를 취득했기 때문에 이 또한 유관부서의 검증이 필요합니다.
  *   현보에 있는 설비에서도 현재 시중에 나와있는 버블엔진을 채택해서 사용 시에 문제가 없을 지에 대한 검증이 필요합니다.
  *   개인적인 의견으로는 현보 설비에서 사용하는 버블 엔진이 적합하지 못하고, 첨부의 신규 엔진 적용에도 현상이 동일하다면 버블을 디텍할 때의 UV 조명 밝기가 상대적으로 낮아서 그럴 수도 있다고 예상 됩니다.
  *   하기의 매뉴얼 대로 하면 자체적인 적용은 쉬운 편 입니다. 서비스 대응이 필요 하시다면 요청 부탁드립니다, 만약 저의 부재나 현장 미방문에 의한 헬프데스크를 통한 원격시엔 적용후의 장기 모니터링은 불가 하다는 부분 사전 전달 드립니다.



  1.  버블엔진을 변경하기

n   유첨의 Model 4d updates 다운받아 설비로 이동하기

n   C:\KohYoung\OCT\OIThicknessMeasurement\OIPredictor\Inspection2d\Bubble\ReClassifier 안에 파일을 넣기

n   [cid:image012.png@01DA3B6C.0F2E4BD0]

n   C:\KohYoung\CCI\Vision 의 VisionConfig2.json 파일을 Notepad++ 로 열기

n   [cid:image013.png@01DA3B6D.097D1F80]

n   하기 경로의 파일명을 model4d 로 바꾸기

n   [cid:image014.png@01DA3B6D.097D1F80]

n   GUI 재실행 하기 (필수)

  1.  버블 엔진 변경으로도 현상이 동일하다면 잡파일의 UV 검사 밝기를 약간 올려보기

n   현재 검증이 필요한 JOB파일에 우측버튼을 눌러 EDIT WITH NOTEPAD++ 로 엽니다 (사전에 잡파일을 백업합니다.)

n   [cid:image010.png@01DA3B6B.22690BA0]

n    UV VALUE=20 을 36 으로 변경 합니다.

n   [cid:image011.png@01DA3B6B.22690BA0]

n   이후 잡파일을 다시 불러오기 하여 가성불량 케이스가 개선 되는 지 확인 (필수)



감사합니다.
이진욱 드림

To: 정종백 <jungjb@hyunbo.com<mailto:jungjb@hyunbo.com>>; TS Helpdesk <korea_help@kohyoung.com<mailto:korea_help@kohyoung.com>>
Cc: '백지명' <bjm@hyunbo.com<mailto:bjm@hyunbo.com>>; '민진기' <mjk@hyunbo.com<mailto:mjk@hyunbo.com>>; '이민재' <mjlee@hyunbo.com<mailto:mjlee@hyunbo.com>>; 국내총괄 <kyk@kohyoung.com<mailto:kyk@kohyoung.com>>; 한경진 _ kyung jin Han <jinny.han@kohyoung.com<mailto:jinny.han@kohyoung.com>>
Subject: RE: Re:Re:버블 가성불량 개선 요청의 件.

수신 : 현보 정종백 부장님

안녕하세요 고영 기술지원팀 이진욱 입니다.

두께 검사 원리는 유첨의 자료 확인 부탁드리며

좀 더 정확한 설명을 드리면, Neptune 의 두께 검사 방식은 NIR (근적외선) 레이저를 이용한 분광법으로 유기체를 확인하는데 유용한 방법 입니다.
근적외선은 가시광선보다 약간 파장이 긴 대역으로 유체를 투과하는데 좀 더 유리한 파장대의 영역 입니다.
각 유체는 고유의 굴절률을 갖고 있는데, 굴절률이란 주어진 소재 내에서 빛의 속도 대비 진공 상태에서의 빛의 속도의 비율로 정의 합니다.
공기의 굴절률은 1로 정의하는데 즉, 다른 유체들은 1보다 크다는 의미가 되며 1보다 크다는 의미는 빛의 속도가 감소한다는 의미이고
빛의 속도가 감소한다는 것은 파장으로 움직이는 빛의 위상에 변화가 생긴다는 뜻입니다.

코팅액 표면에서 반사되는 빛과 , 부품 상면에서 반사되는 빛.  즉, 대상체 간에 위상차가 발생 하면서
특정한 위상에서는 보강간섭(max 한파장) 이 발생하여 밝게 보일 것이고 또 다른 특정한 위상에선 소멸간섭(max 반파장)이 발생하여 어둡게 보일 것 입니다.
이를 저희 Camera 에 있는 Photo Sensor 가 빛의 위상차를 감지하고 밝게 보이는 부분과 어둡게 보이는 부분을 Data Processing 하여 처리하게 되면
저희 Debug image 에서 볼 수 있는 두께 상면의 영역과 코팅 상면의 영역을 확인 할 수 있게 되며 그 편차를 계산하면 두께 값을 산출 할 수 있습니다.
마이켈슨 간섭계의 원리와 유사 하오니 참고 하시면 도움이 될 것 같습니다.


[cid:image001.png@01DA3B6A.C7336FA0]
[cid:image002.png@01DA3B6A.C7336FA0]

Neptune 두께검사의 제약점 중 한가지는 높이 부분에서 검사영역에 제한이 있다는 부분 입니다.
Camera 가 특정 높이에서 대상체를 볼 때 갖고 있는 특성으로써 검사기가 Focusing 가능한 영역을 위나 아래로 벗어나버리면 검사영역에서 벗어나 버려 올바른 검사를 진행 할 수 없게 됩니다.
즉, 제품이 들떴을 때 0 이 나왔다가 안착을 다시 진행 한 후 검사 했을 때 양품이 나오는 현상은 지극히 설비 측면에서 자연스러운 현상이며
안착을 개선하거나, 제품이 들뜰 걸 대비하여 카메라위치를 위로 이동시켜 검사영역에 코팅 경계 영역이 들어 올 수 있게 하는 방법이 있습니다.
카메라 위치를 MCS란 모션제어시스템에서 고정으로 위치를 잡거나 다른 부품에는 제약이 있을 우려가 있을 때 특정 부품만 Probe 를 이동시켜 좀 더 높은 영역에서 경계를 찾도록 설정할 수 있습니다.
설정에 의한 추가 제약점은 특정 부품의 코팅 경계만 찾으러 Probe 를 이동 시킬 때는 대상체에서 Probe Moving 이 추가로 발생 되기 때문에 CT 가 다소 늘어나게 되며
안착이 불량할 걸 예상하고 너무 높은 영역에 MCS 세팅으로 Camera 를 두고 검사를 하게 되면, 정상 안착품이 오히려 코팅경계를 추출하기 좋은 Focusing 영역에서 벗어 날 가능성 또한 존재 합니다.

[cid:image003.png@01DA3B6A.C7336FA0]

상기의 설명 부분이 누락된 것으로 보여 추가적으로 메일 회신 드립니다.



*추가로 일전에 요청하셨던 리뷰 바코드 정보 는 하기의 세팅을 참고하셔서 출력여부 검토 부탁드리고, 버블 사이즈 um 표기는 아직 개발 완료가 되지 않은 상황이라
추가적으로 내용 업데이트 드리도록 하겠습니다.
[cid:image004.png@01DA3B6A.C7336FA0]







감사합니다.
이진욱 드림

subject: [Asahi Kasei]OddShape의 Area Unit에 Body Location의 Offset이 반영되지 않는 문제
description_text: 배경 및 내용  Asahi Kasei고객사에서 Chip 부품의 색상검사를 Try하고 있습니다.  색상의 지정이 용이한 점에서 OddShape의 Area Unit으로 검사를 진행하고 있습니다.  Location Offset / Body Unit Offset 모두 True로 설정하여 검사를 진행하고 있습니다.      실제 검사를 진행할 경우, Body Location에 추종이 되지 않는 ROI의 위치에서 검사를 진행하는 것이 확인이 됩니다.  Body Presetting은 Full 3D (Fixed)로 Body Location을 찾도록 설정이 되어져 있습니다.   Pad Overhang결과 캡쳐   OddShape Unit의 극성 검사 결과 캡쳐         해당 동작은 2.7.4.3 및 2.8.1.1 버전에서도 동일하게 확인이 되기에, ER안건으로 보여지나, 정보 확인 지원이 필요합니다.      관련하여, 2개의 CBI를 하기의 링크로 첨부 드립니다.  (Body Offset을 Presetting-3D Full모드,  OddShape-Offset, 각각에 대해서 업로드 드립니다.)  20231228 [Ashahi Kasei]MELF CBI      현장 서포트로써는, OddShape-Offset 그룹 적용 및 MELF자체의 색상 검사에 대해서 트라이 해 보도록 하겠습니다.

subject: Flex Ofaqim: Calibration issue
description_text: Hi to All,     First of all, Happy New Year!      I have a huge issue related to machine calibration and I need your help. Two weeks ago I went to the customer to calibrate all Kohyoung machines and to change 3D LED projectors by the way if needed. The customer has five dual-lane AOI machines that they received from China without the original HDD (without OS and machine information). Almost all nine machines were calibrated as PASS, but three machines had illumination issues (3D LED illumination fail) and I started to change the projector. Meanwhile, I changed projectors only in one machine (AP-DL-00309) and asked Ali to help me because the illumination calibration failed. Ali advised me to check the grating values in the registry, we changed the value but it did not help. Now  I need somebody will connect and we try to calibrate the machine.     Let's try to do this in the next week, and I will arrange the remote to the machine.

subject: [Request]: SPI remote connection.
description_text:
Buen día equipo Kohyoung,

Retomando actividades después de un largo periodo de descanso, me gustaría darle seguimiento a una actividad que no se pudo concluir al final del año pasado por el receso de actividades.

Básicamente es por un error de posición que está marcando la SPI después de hacer la inspección el cual marca un error superior al 33% de desfasamiento en X, se hizo la confirmación en un equipo manual y no se detecto ese desfase.

[cid:image001.jpg@01DA4477.1EB50DF0][cid:image002.jpg@01DA4477.1EB50DF0]

Me gustaría saber si esto se puede solucionar haciendo una corrección del programa sin modificar los parámetros de inspección, anteriormente me dieron la opción de hacer una conexión remota para poder checar el comportamiento de la máquina.

Quedo al pendiente de sus comentarios.

Saludos cordiales,

Flavio G.

subject: Custom AOI reports - SPC software or KSMART
description_text: Hello     The quality team at LSI ADL Technology has tracked AOI defects with the old YesTech AOI machines using an SQL database.  We can search by work order and it provides a report of what defects were reported during AOI by defect type and by reference designator.     We would like to setup a report similar to this format (by defect and by reference designator) using either the SPC software or the report features in KSMART. I can get SPC to generate a report showing the top five defects discovered during a work order but have not found a way to show a full defect report that lists by reference designator.  Do you have any sample report templates that fit these requirements?  Thank you,     Mark Fergus

subject: RE: Programas de AOI con Inspeccion Absence
description_text:
Buen día equipo KY
hay alguna actualización sobre este caso? Seguimos presentando el mismo problema y nos afecta en nuestro FPY, como información adicional:


  1.  La falla se presenta a mediación de corrida (no primera pieza en cambio de modelo)
  2.  Utilizamos deploy para mover los Job entre equipos, pero en todas las líneas se inspeccionan los mismos componentes y solo L1 presenta este problema
  3.  No utilizamos Job con tagset
  4.  Al momento de ser detectado por AOI la casilla de absense aparece deshabilitada, por lo que no es la condición inicial del componente, la manera ¨temporal¨ de solucionarlo es como menciona Luis habilitar y deshabilitar la casilla de absense o bien aplicando setcad al cuerpo del componente
[cid:image001.png@01DA3220.57C32500]

Ejemplo de falla presentada a mediación de corrida:
[cid:image006.png@01DA3221.1110BC70]
[cid:image007.png@01DA3221.5C444AE0]

Quedamos en espera de respuesta, si es necesaria alguna información adicional favor de hacérnosla saber

AOI Team

Adrián Martínez
AOI Technician, PASMT, SMT
E. Adrian.Martinez@panasonicautomotive.com<mailto:Adrian.Martinez@panasonicautomotive.com>
Isidoro Sepúlveda 851, Regio Parque
Industrial | Apodaca, N.L.
Panasonic AUTOMOTIVE

From: Luis Rodrigo Hernandez Obispo <Luis.HernandezO@panasonicautomotive.com>
Sent: Monday, December 11, 2023 12:57 PM
To: America Support <kya_support@kohyoung.com>
Cc: Silva Alva, Fernando <SilvaF@panasonicautomotive.com>; #TEAM AOI <TEAMAOI@PASA365.onmicrosoft.com>
Subject: Programas de AOI con Inspeccion Absence

Buen día;

Solicitamos soporte de su parte para resolver un issue en programas de AOI.
Esta situación ya se había reportado, pero no nos han dado solución debido a que sigue apareciendo en los programas.

La problemática es que tenemos componente que lleva la prueba de Absence. Pero en el mismo programa, se han presentado que en componentes que, si van montados,
el programa aplica el algoritmo de absence cuando no debe de ser. La posible solución que le damos en el momento es quitar la prueba de absence y volver a inspeccionar.


[cid:image002.png@01DA321C.7971B8A0]
Este es el componente que se había reportado.

Al principio y la vez que lo reportamos afectaba un solo numero de parte, pero este fin de semana, se agregaron mas a la lista de componentes afectados.

[cid:image003.png@01DA321C.7971B8A0]                [cid:image004.png@01DA321C.7971B8A0]
Nos podrían apoyar con este issue.

¿De la misma forma, quiero saber si hay algún Pre-setting que estemos ajustando mal y es por eso que nos falla el algoritmo?

Les comparto la versión de GUI del euipo. Ya que este es el único que hemos visto que aplica esta prueba.

[cid:image005.png@01DA321C.7971B8A0]

Cualquier duda o comentario hacérmelo saber.

Luis Hernandez
AOI Technician, PASMT, SMT
E. Luis.Hernandez@panasonicautomotive.com<mailto:Adrian.Martinez@panasonicautomotive.com>
Isidoro Sepúlveda 851, Regio Parque
Industrial | Apodaca, N.L.
Panasonic AUTOMOTIVE

subject: [바텍이엔지] AOI 플립 모드 설정 시 비정상 작동 로그 분석 요청의 건
description_text: 안녕하세요 AOI SW 프론트 담당자님     국내 TS팀 박종현 사원입니다.      AOI 플립 모드 활성화 이후 DB 저장 및 MCS 이상 알람 발생 문제가 발생하여 로그 분석을 요청 드립니다.     문제 설비는 전단 Flipper 설비와 연동 중이며 1차면 Flipper 이동 2차면 검사 후 배출 시퀀스입니다.     버젼 업데이트 내역  AOI GUI   2.7.4.3 > 2.7.5.0_H03_T-87-g9052514750   과거 전단 반전기 연동 시 MCS Job 이슈 존재해 개선이 완료 된 버젼으로 업데이트     MCS  770 > 800.0.15       현장 이슈 진행 상황  AOI GUI 2.7.5 버젼 업데이트 이후 플립 모드 실행 시 DB 저장 및 MCS 알람 발생  MCS 버젼 770 > 800.0.15 업데이트 이후 Job 실행 시 정상 구동  플립 모드 비활성화 > 재활성화 진행 후 Job 오픈 이후 구동 시 MCS 버젼 업데이트 전과 동일한 문제 발생    발생 시간  1/5 16시 20분 MCS 버젼 업데이트 이후 정상 시퀀스 동작  1/5  17시 10분 플립 모드 관련 옵션 재가동 이후 DB 저장 및 MCS 에러 발생    첨부파일  20240105 AOI 전단 반전기 사용 불가 이슈

subject: FW: Queries regarding IPC-CFX BRM for Koh Young
description_text:
From: Tyson Madge <tmadge@redarc.com.au>
Sent: Friday, September 15, 2023 11:54 AM
To: Jack Chin_Chun Lek Chin <chunlek.chin@kohyoung.com>; Wilson Khor _ Chin Cheng Khor <wilson@kohyoung.com>
Cc: CY Ng_Choo Yee Ng <cy.ng@kohyoung.com>; Chris Morrison <cmorrison@redarc.com.au>; Heinz Zimmermann <HZimmermann@suba.com.au>; Tech Support <techsupport@suba.com.au>
Subject: Queries regarding IPC-CFX BRM for Koh Young

Dear all, I hope you are well.

I had a couple of queries about the IPC-CFX BRM which we have recently had installed on our SMT lines. Although I know there is still some work to be done on configuring the AOI BRM which Edwin is kindly liaising with Koh Young for,  I believe things are running pretty well on our SPI machines so far.

The questions I had were around some of the data we're getting out of the equipment:


  1.  It seems that for certain messages from the Koh Young equipment, the messages aren't contextualising what the PCB IDs are that the equipment is performing these actions for. For instance when units are arriving, or departing, or begin being processed or complete being processed the messages don't include the serial IDs of the units which are arriving or departing e.g.:

{
    "MessageName": "CFX.Production.UnitsDeparted",
    "Version": "1.4",
    "TimeStamp": "2023-09-15T11:19:42.2655986+09:30",
    "UniqueID": "73dd0904-c59e-4101-9a25-8294e17ce753",
    "Source": "Kohyoung.KY8030-3.SS-SL-04739",
    "Target": null,
    "RequestID": null,
    "MessageBody": {
        "$type": "CFX.Production.UnitsDeparted, CFX",
        "PrimaryIdentifier": null,
        "HermesIdentifier": null,
        "UnitCount": 0,
        "Units": [],
        "Lane": 1
    }
}

or:

{
    "MessageName": "CFX.Production.UnitsArrived",
    "Version": "1.4",
    "TimeStamp": "2023-09-15T11:18:46.9115116+09:30",
    "UniqueID": "fdc9218b-0f5a-4441-9a1b-3f0a6e4d280e",
    "Source": "Kohyoung.KY8030-3.SS-SL-04739",
    "Target": null,
    "RequestID": null,
    "MessageBody": {
        "$type": "CFX.Production.UnitsArrived, CFX",
        "PrimaryIdentifier": null,
        "HermesIdentifier": null,
        "UnitCount": 2,
        "Units": [
            {
                "UnitIdentifier": null,
                "PositionNumber": 1,
                "PositionName": "CIRCUIT1",
                "X": 0,
                "Y": 0,
                "Rotation": 0,
                "FlipX": false,
                "FlipY": false,
                "Status": "Pass"
            },
            {
                "UnitIdentifier": null,
                "PositionNumber": 2,
                "PositionName": "CIRCUIT2",
                "X": 0,
                "Y": 0,
                "Rotation": 0,
                "FlipX": false,
                "FlipY": false,
                "Status": "Pass"
            }
        ],
        "Lane": 1
    }
},

                Is it possible to have the Koh Young machines provide the context of the unit ID for these messages?


  1.  I wondering if Koh Young could please provide a list for us of all the equipment states based on their codes for us? Currently equipment state changes are a 4 digit number, it would be good to understand if for instance equipment state: 5000 = run mode or: 2000 = standby etc.



  1.  Looking at the data, it seems that the equipment outputs messages for when units are inspected by the equipment which is good, however we're not seeing any subsequent messages posted and results sent for judgement calls made by the operators. Referring back to our original request form, what we are hoping for is to see when a unit leaves the SPI whether the unit has been sent to rework or has been passed by the operator.



What this could mean is that when a board is held due to a machine NG, the equipment does not emit a UnitsDeparted message until the judgement call is made by the operator. Then as part of the structure of the UnitsDeparted message under the Units field there is an array of all circuits in the panel with a unit identified and the status of the circuit. For example in case a board were held in the buffer because of a defect, the operator would review the defects and make a judgement. Once that is complete and operator selects either pass or NG the equipment would emit a message such as:


{
    "MessageName": "CFX.Production.UnitsDeparted",
    "Version": "1.4",
    "TimeStamp": "2023-09-15T11:18:46.9115116+09:30",
    "UniqueID": "fdc9218b-0f5a-4441-9a1b-3f0a6e4d280e",
    "Source": "Kohyoung.KY8030-3.SS-SL-04739",
    "Target": null,
    "RequestID": null,
    "MessageBody": {
        "$type": "CFX.Production.UnitsDeparted, CFX",
        "PrimaryIdentifier": null,
        "HermesIdentifier": null,
        "UnitCount": 2,
        "Units": [
            {
                "UnitIdentifier": "D15092023T121827N1B1123P201", // note the UnitIdentifier is the same as the ones used in the CFX.Production.TestAndInspection.UnitsInspected message.
                "PositionNumber": 1,
                "PositionName": "CIRCUIT1",
                "X": 0,
                "Y": 0,
                "Rotation": 0,
                "FlipX": false,
                "FlipY": false,
                "Status": "Pass"
            },
            {
                "UnitIdentifier": "D15092023T121827N2B1123P201",
                "PositionNumber": 2,
                "PositionName": "CIRCUIT2",
                "X": 0,
                "Y": 0,
                "Rotation": 0,
                "FlipX": false,
                "FlipY": false,
                "Status": "Fail" // Status would be determined based on the operator determination after reviewing all defects.
            }
        ],
        "Lane": 1
    }

},



Our MES would then interpret that if any units in the array had the status of fail that the panel is sent to rework. If all are pass it will move the material to the next process. The equipment would still also send a message for the machine inspection results, this would be in addition to what the equipment is currently doing.



Is it possible that we have this part of the BRM adjusted for this requirement? I would be more than happy to join a quick Teams meeting to explain further if necessary.

Overall we're very pleased with the BRM, we're making good progress and it's great to be able to capture this event data which will be an integral part of our MES project. Any help you are able to give me in the matters above is greatly appreciated. Thanks very much and have a nice day and a good weekend.

Best regards,
Tyson Madge
I4.0 Technician

subject: [AOI/OLP] Problem when adding new components - "Wrong CAD data" and mismatched image - USI Poland
description_text:
Dear KYE Support,

USI Poland has bought an OLP computer and they would like to do some offline programming for their AOI machines. They have encountered a problem though. I have been there and configured their OLP in the following way:

  1.  I have copied AOIGUISetup.ini file, ref and ini folders from C:\KohYoung\AOI\Vision from the machine to their OLP computer. Of course I did change a few things here and there to make it work properly.
  2.  I checked that after grabbing the FOV images on the machine and copying the job folder to OLP, I can open it up in AOIGUI on OLP and run normal inspection as expected.

Let me explain what the problem is:

  1.  They have created a new KYPCB file in ePM for a completely new board.
  2.  This file has been imported to AOIGUI and some of the packages were automatically assigned as expected.
  3.  The customer grabbed inspection FOV images con the AOI and copied the job folder to OLP.
  4.  They opened up the job file on OLP and they can inspect existing components without any problems:
[cid:image007.png@01DA3FDE.7D255860]

  5.  The problem is that when they created a new package for a component, which was in the exact same FOV as the abovementioned one (both marked red below):
[cid:image008.png@01DA3FDF.9E8145E0]
[cid:image011.png@01DA3FDF.C857B8E0]

They get something like this when inspecting it:
[cid:image010.png@01DA3FDF.9E8145E0]

We have "Wrong CAD data" (just like when the lead tips are outside of their respective pads) and in the 2D image we have a completely different part of the PCB shown.

I assume this is because physically this new component wasn't included in any FOV when the FOV image grab was done. Is there any way we can overcome this problem?

Currently it looks like they need to do 2 FOV grabs: first one after importing the KYPCB file, then they need to create all the packages that are missing, do the second FOV grab on the machine and fine-tune everything that was created. Am I correct or am I missing something?

Please explain.

Thank you in advance.

Pozdrawiam/Best regards

---

Daniel Kotwicki

CONFIDENTIALITY:  Internal – Forward only to internal colleagues

Buen día

Durante nuestro arranque de equipos, se tuvo el siguiente error en SPI de L9, al momento de abrir la aplicación de WinMCS, al mostrar el error, se cierra la aplicación.
Se reinicio el equipo y se reviso que los drivers no mostraran ningun error en el equipo durante el inicio de la aplicación, estos no mostraron ningun error.

subject: Padget Electronics Noida sector 68, SS-DL-01578,KY SPI 8030-2, PZT Move Error, Visibility is under 0.04 (unable to run Production)
description_text: Dear Sir,  Customer Name:- Padget Electronics 68  Machine Name and Serial Number:-KY SPI 8030-2 SS-DL-01578.  Issue Description:  We were facing Bridging issue and image construction issue in Line-8 KY SPI, in each Pannel.  Z-Cal issue also there while performing SPI Calibration in Line-8.  PZT move errors and visibility also NG.  we found visibility was not ok, it was around 0.04.   As discussed with Prabhanshu San we checked all the things related to this,  Each connections reconnected and PZT motor also reconnected, but issue was still same,  So, we swapped PZT motor and Amplifier unit with Line-12 SPI.  After this activity calibration got ok, but Machine running in Mass Production.  Then we tried to do calibration in line-12 but facing same issues.  So, we came to know PZT is not working so we need to replace it ASAP.  Customer have to run line and in this situation, we cannot run line.     I have attached images for the defected parts.  let me know for any more information's..        Thanks,  DEVESH PANT  PSFSIN

subject: (Harimagroup) - Request for New SPI Calibration support -  SN:SPI4T30
description_text:
Hello KYE,

I am at the customer site trying to perform service and calibration on a tabletop SPI but facing some issues with the calibration steps.

Software Information

GUI: 3.5.2146P5
WINmcs : 760.09.95

KYCAL : 1.0.0

We all know this machine is a very old machine but due to the machine being still alive the customer still uses the machine.

In this case, we offer service and calibration on the machine annually, this customer is part of our global account, and we try to support them as best as we can.


I have managed to complete PZT calibration by using the GUI software but when I try to use the KY Cal software to complete the rest of the calibration process I face the following challenges.


  *   Camera calibration target- how do I get the power connection for the camera target on this system?
  *   New SPI calibration process manual
  *   I got the below errors when I tried to perform the calibration steps on the system.


  1.  Illumination calibration
  2.  Z-Calibration

I will be on customer site tomorrow morning by 10:00 UK time , please can anyone advice or provide necessary information on this process.

subject: Zenith AOI Review Stations
description_text:
Good afternoon,

I have a couple of questions:

What causes an ROI or sets of ROI boxes to not display correctly? We are noticing that if, for example, a call for Polarity has occurred there are times when the ROI boxes are not displayed unless we exit the condition screen and then reselect the defect from the list. On occasion we've had to reinspect the PCBA.

The buttons for work in and work out, as well as the play button in the GUI do not always work on the first click. Is this a normal glitch? The buttons will actuate on the screen, but no functionality of the button executes. We end up having to click again or do double clicks.

We are having a minor issue with being able to review classified PCBAs at our Review Stations. I have looked through all the Settings for the stations and I cannot seem to solve our issue. We are using Review Station Version 2.6.1.0
As we are processing PCBAs through the Zenith AOI, when a PCBA goes to the "No Good" side and we utilize the Review Station to classify the PCBA, we have noticed that if the PCBA is classified as "Good" we can no longer scan in the PCBA to the Review Station and see the record. In the past we have been able to scan a processed PCBA into the Review Station and see the defect record regardless of classification. Whether the PCBA had defects and classified as such or having defects and being "False Called", both records would show. Currently, PCBAs that have been classified as "Good" at the review Station, if re-scanned into the Review after classification, we no longer can see the defect results. How do I fix that?

Do the Zenith GUI and Review Station need to have compatible config files to work congruently?

In the Review Set Up under "Basic" tab what function do the following serve?
                "Use Load NG with Pass"
                "Use Load All Panel Result"

Under GUI Config.
"Save a changed inspection log file?" This is set to False. We want to eliminate the question asking to save changes after we've made a change. Is this where we can do that?

FYI, these challenges happened after our hardware upgrade in December 2023.

Thank you,

Aaron J Lafond "aj"
Manufacturing Technician III
Enercon Technologies
39 Northbrook Dr.
Gray, Maine 04039
207-657-7000
480-205-5160

subject: Storage Capacity for NG and false call pictures
description_text:
Dear Team,

Our customer is asking for information about the storage capacity of the KSmart Advanced Server system needed for NG and false call images.

The customer has inquired about the system's suitability for storing these images for a duration of two years. Given that certain parameters could vary, we aim to provide approximate figures to assist them in estimating their storage needs accurately. Could you please share information regarding the items below:

Any information you can provide regarding this subject will help us better meet our customer's needs.

subject: CDM Export IMI Bulgaria
description_text:
Hello all,     We've got a request from IMI Bulgaria about the topic below.     CDM Export conducts board inspections, which typically take up to 2 minutes per panel to save the results. During this process, the processor operates at maximum capacity (100%). If you disable the "Settings-Darta/Export – Good + Details" option to prevent result collection, there are no issues.This occurs across all GUI software versions, and we operate on the WIN 7 platform. The problem is consistent across all AOIs utilizing this feature. It tends to occur more frequently on programs with a higher number of components and those lacking pairing inspection. Is it possible to calculate the Good+Details metrics on a per-job basis rather than general.
     Best Regards,  Atanas Titov

subject: LED error on Review station IMI Bulgaria
description_text:
Hello all,     One more request from IMI.     There is an issue with the Review Station software. When LED rotation alarm surpasses the specified degree or distance threshold from the phosphor to the body or CAD, the operator is unable to clear the error. The only option is to mark it as a general NG and block the entire panel. This problem is when configuring the Led -Others-Sub Inspection-LedPhosphor-Amp setting.
  If there is a problem with Dimension of the LED for the distance of the phosphor to the body in length, width or rotation, the result of the Review Station is not clear what it is. Only Dimension or Distance is displayed and the defect does not disappear after classification. Only general NG can be given. The Review station version is seen in the pictures (2.6.1) and on AOIGUI 2.7.6.0_H01.
     Best Regards,  Atanas Titov

subject: AOI Database grows activating saving OK results.
description_text:
Hello,

I have a doubt about the database saving data on AOI.

In our customer Borgwarner the settings for saving the data in database is saving only NG results (+ images 3D and 2D) as you can see in the following image:

[cid:image001.png@01DA082A.8BF3F2C0]

As the fault rate is not big, they keep weekly database size with small size.

If we activate the option "Good Results" and "details" the size grows a lot, in fact, it increased 4GB in only one shift. Settings was as the image below:

[cid:image002.png@01DA082A.F31D6710]

How it is possible that it grows that fast only saving data (without images)?

Thanks in advance

Best regards

Jose Manuel Calle
Propelec S.L.

subject: Flex Ofaqim: AOI barcode reading
description_text: Hi to All,     The customer wants to start reading barcodes for all boards on the AOI machines.  The issue they are having is that some PCBs have a barcode only on one side of the board.  In this case, the customer needs to know if they can scan the barcode before the machine with an external Camera or Reader.     Can you please provide information on the following questions:      What external tools can be used for reading a barcode and providing it to the machine (HERMES / CFX / Barcode Reader / Camera with barcode reading capability)?  How do I connect each type of tool to the machine? Physical connection - to where? Software application – how?  Is It possible to configure the machines so that for some Programs the barcode will be read by the machine and others by external?  If the Program is configured to receive the Barcode from external, can the machine be configured to pull the Board only after receiving the Barcode?      Any extra documentation you can give me would be greatly appreciated.

subject: Review Station DataBase backup on network drive
description_text:
Hi, Good morning.

Our customer Bosch in Ovar (Portugal) is using DB manager to automatically backup the database files and then delete de old databases (previously backup).

The problem is that the backup is done in a local folder and this way they cannot save disk space, so, they want to do the backup on a network drive, but DB Manager do not allow to select networks drive for backup.

I tried to us Microsoft SQL Management Studio to perform the backup manually, but it neither allows to select network drives for backups.

My question is, do you know if there is some way to perform the backup to a network drive?

We know that the alternative is doing the backup locally and then moving the files to the network drive, but maybe you know a better solution.

Thanks in advance,

Best regards

Jose Manuel Calle
Propelec S.L.

subject: Customer Sirico: Ksmart core time is wrong and keeps reverting to wrong time if adjusted
description_text: Good morning,  Description: Customer Sirico reports that Ksmart Core time is always wrong, causing issues with loading inspection results from SQL db.  On several occasions I have changed the time on: 1. Review PC 2. Checked that Ksmart Core follows = Correct time 3. Checked that AOI is synchronized to Ksmart core = Correct time ...But Ksmart keeps reverting to incorrect time after a day.  Conditions:  I have deactivated the use of ntp-server in Ksmart (I recall an old bug in Ksmart regardin the use of ntp-server) Up until today "Synchronize with time serve"r has been active        - I have deactivated the use of time synchronization in Hyper V (a quick google generates multiple hits on Hyper V & time issues)  - Up until today Hyper V time synchronization has been activated (testing if turning it of has any effect).       - I have re-adjusted Review PC windows time again  - Checked Ksmart core time again  - Checked AOI time again  Right now all time is correct, but for how long is the question...        Files: Webmanager log uploaded to wetransfer: https://we.tl/t-biWhEdEVBb     Questions: - What is the ideal Master time when Ksmart core is used? - I'm thinking that it should be Review PC windows time, since Hyper V is installed on the PC? - If review PC is the Master Time, should we really use KSA (risk of feedback loop regarding time?)  - What is the correct config to force AOI, Review & Ksmart Core to keep correct time? subject: AOIGUI version - 2.7.6
description_text:
Hi guys,


customer reported bugs on AOIGUI 2.7.5.0_H03. Machine is Alpha.


They have following issues:

- random FOV sometimes gets deleted (components are not inspected) - for example, they have 30 FOV, next time they produce this product they have 29 FOv - when they check FOV they see that 1 is missing (some components not inspected) - they manually recreate FOV then it is fine

- when using alternative components - polarity is gone from already programmed component and they have to program it again

- when they close AOIGUI and reopen newly added components (before closing AOIGUI) are rotated for 90 degrees


Can you please advise which 2.7.5 or 2.7.6 version can they test?


Thanks a lot,


Mit freundlichen Grüßen/Best regards

subject: Enabling 'Bad Mark' option on 3D AOI
description_text:
Good morning,

I have a question regarding the use of the 'Bad Mark' feature on the AOI software.

I have attached screenshots showing 2 different assemblies. One of these assemblies (1572-0151RD) has the ability to enable and use the Bad Mark option in order to disregard a board that is potentially marked off and not populated. I want to enable this feature for usage on the other assembly (130-0083 Rev B4) but I cannot seem to figure out where this bad mark feature is enabled and how to get it working for this new assembly.

I am unsure as to weather this 'Bad Mark' feature is enabled early on in the EPM software when creating the .KYPCB file, or if this is something that is setup within the AOI GUI.

Any help in figuring this out would be greatly appreciated.

Thank you!

Regards,

CONOR MORRISSEY
Manufacturing Engineer | P: 617.598.3063 | E: cmorrissey@ewmfg.com<mailto:kko@ewmfg.com>

subject: FALLA RECONOCIMIENTO POR OCR
description_text:
Buenos dias equipo de soporte,

En el turno de noche se reporta un issue sobre un componente montado equivocadamente.

Para detectarlo sabemos que tenemos la prueba de OCR, mas sin embargo AOI no fue capaz de detectar dicho defecto, la serigrafia que estamos buscando es un 102, pero se monto un 201, en la captura podemos apreciar que la referencia que no coincide con el dibujo y aun así la AOI lo esta detectando como GOOD, para los resistores no le colocamos prueba de polaridad ya que sabemos que no tienen.

[cid:image001.png@01DA4797.A57BD1C0]

Cree que el tipo de fuente esta afectando a la inspección?
Vemos un parámetro de tipo de fuente como industrial, hay alguna revisión mas actual en donde podamos ver mas opciones para el tipo de fuente?
Tienen alguna recomendación para poder inspeccionar de manera correcta este componente?
Quedo atenta a los comentarios.
Gracias!

subject: AOI MES 수정 요청
description_text: 안녕하십니까. 티앤에프 이건헌입니다.     AOI MES 수정 건으로 문의드립니다.     현재 2차면 검사 시 1차면이 NG로 등록되어 있으면 검사하지 않고 NG Buffer로 배출하게 되어있습니다.     수정 요청드리는 부분은 검사하지 않고 NG Buffer로 배출하는 것이 아닌 정상적으로 검사 후에 NG Buffer로 배출하게 수정 요청드리며,     자세한 내용은 재협의가 필요해보입니다. 추가 요청사항시 회신 부탁드립니다.     이상입니다.

subject: Zenith AOI FM Feature
description_text:
Hello,

Is there a way to change the FM Max Area, Max Length etc "greater than symbol" to work as a less than symbol.
I realize the algorithm is looking for FM greater than a certain size.
I want to detect the size smaller than the value, therefore I am passing bad and failing good.

I was using the FM area to try and determine if an area on an LED is good or bad based on delamination.
The area is different between good and bad.

Any idea on another feature that could be used? I basically want to detect an area that appears to be smaller due to warp deep inside an LED versus a good LED which is flat.

Ken Klima
Rockwell Automation

subject: Issue connecting via Remote Desktop to Koh Young Inspection Machine NP-SL-00083
description_text:
ZF Confidential

I am trying to set up the Conformal Coat Inspection System and am having a few problems with application settings and connecting to a database.   To work through those, I planned to connect to the machine via Remote Desktop and work with Koh Young Application Engineers to solve these issues.   I can connect via Remote Desktop, but I do not have the appropriate privileges apparently.  The desktop that I can see remotely does not contain the same application shortcuts and it appears that the connection is primarily read only.   I can only manage to connect as Guest with no password requirements.   This is what the desktop looks like when connected Remotely:

[cid:image001.png@01DA47AC.10843DE0]


I would like to work with someone to address the following issues:


  1.  How to connect to be able to review and edit remotely.   I suspect that I need an administrator level UID and password.
  2.  Identify and confirm proper start up of all the software.  Currently it seems that the Neptune C+ software isn’t starting properly.
  3.  Set and confirm the appropriate Network File storage locations for the inspection data in preparation of placing it into our manufacturing line.

For reference, I have been working a bit with Daniel Perry and Luis Rodriguez on this machine.  They will have some familiarity with the issues that we have had, and the actions taken so far.

Please review and contact me with a plan to assist with these requests.   I look forward to hearing from you soon.   Thanks.

Kind regards,

Kevin Waltz

Principal Manufacturing Engineer
Final Assembly Process Engineering

ZF Group
Electronics & ADAS Division
ZF Active Safety and Electronics US LLC
902 South 2nd St., Marshall, IL 62441 / USA
Phone +1 217 826 1652, Fax +1 217 826 1653
Cell +1 812 240 6619
kevin.waltz@zf.com<mailto:John.Hawkins@TRW.com>

description_text:
Inge. Salvador/Jose, 
 
 
 
   
 
 El dia de hoy se le dio seguimiento a este problema. KohYoug Korea envio versión: 
 
 
  
   
 
 KY_SPI_Setup_x86_5.0.0.0_H01_T41_5af32b9

subject: Re: POs pendientes.
description_text:
Buenas tardes a todos, 
 
 
 
 
@Manuel Celis, te comparto un breve resumen de los assessment realizados en las SPI N/S SS-SL-03119 & SS-SL-03181. 
 
 
 
 
Ambos equipos presentan problemas de Windows ya que al realizar cualquier tarea se traban constantemente y tardan en responder, no solo de las aplicaciones de KY si no con cualquier acción que se realice,
incluso en la SPI de línea 5 (SS-SL-03119) esta infectado de virus ya que la memoria RAM siempre muestra arriba de 10GB de uso aun cuando no hay aplicaciones abiertas, por
 tal motivo se recomienda cargar imagen de fabrica en ambos equipos. 
 
 
 
 
SS-SL-03119
 
 
 
 El HDD presenta un error al bootear Windows (se recomienda cambiar HDD y cargar imagen de fabrica) 
 Falta de mantenimiento general (La maquina esta extremadamente sucia por dentro y fuera de la maquina) 
 La PC también se encuentra con demasiado polvo 
 Filtros sucios 
 Maquina no se calibraba desde su fecha de instalación 
 La calibración no pasaba se tuvieron que limpiar los espejos y aun así paso con valores marginales (se recomienda cambiar módulos de espejos y mantenimiento completo a sistema de vision) 
 Virus encontrado (Muestra uso de Memoria RAM por encima de 10GB aun sin aplicaciones abiertas) 
 PC solo cuenta con 16GB RAM (se recomienda incrementar al menos a 32GB) 
 Se eliminan archivos temporales y basura para aumentar el espacio en el HDD. 
 Se actualizan versiones a las mas recientes 
 
 SS-SL-03181 
 
 
 
 Windows tarda mas de lo normal en apagar y arrancar (se recomienda cargar imagen de fabrica, esta maquina ya fue actualizada a Win10, al instalar la imagen de fabrica la cual es Win7 se va a requerir hacer
 el upgrade de nuevo a Win10) 
 Falta de mantenimiento general (La maquina esta extremadamente sucia por dentro y fuera de la maquina) 
 La PC también se encuentra con demasiado polvo 
 Filtros sucios o faltantes 
 Maquina no se calibraba desde su fecha de instalación 
 La calibración no pasaba se tuvieron que limpiar los espejos y aun así paso con valores marginales (se recomienda cambiar módulos de espejos y
 mantenimiento completo a sistema de vision) 
 
Se eliminan archivos temporales y basura para aumentar el espacio en el HDD. 
 
 Se actualizan versiones a las mas recientes 
 
Es posible que el problema de que Windows se trabe y esto ocasione que las aplicaciones no respondan en tiempo normal aun siga ocurriendo, como lo comento en las primeras lineas del correo, para corregir este problema es necesario cargar imágenes de fabrica
 en ambos equipos. 
 
 
 
 
Trabajare en el reporte y en las partes recomendadas para enviarles las cotizaciones ASAP. 
 
 
 
 
Cualquier duda estoy a la orden.

subject: [일신테크놀러지_화성] Bare Board 검사 시 Noise 현상 확인 요청 건
description_text: 수신 : SPI Vision 프론트 데스크 담당자님        안녕하세요 국내 TS 이진욱 입니다.     하기와 같이 Bare Board 검사 시 Pad 에서 Noise 가 발생 중인데,  ceditor 나 Vision 에서 noise removal , visibility 속성을 변경하며 보아도   제거가 정상적으로 되지 않는 것으로 보여 Sim.Data 를 취득 했으니 Debugging 방법이나 그 외 Solution 도출을 요청 드립니다.   미납으로 빠지지 않고 그외 불량으로 나와 문제가 되고 있습니다.     해당 건은 신규 설비 셋업 및 양산 전 검증 작업으로 고객이 엔드유저에게 제출해야하는 자료 취합 중 발생한 건으로 무조건 해결이 되어야 하는 사안이니  SIM DATA 로 분석이 어려울 시에는 필히 연락 주시어 원격 혹은 방문으로 개선 가능하도록 도움 부탁 드립니다.  격무에 바쁘시겠지만 헬프데스크 담당하는 분께서 가능 하시면 명일 까지는 확인 부탁 드립니다.     버전정보,잡,시뮬데이터 링크 : https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1hJ029ahRYYVJ9bvbXI6Q2UAULuKTunV1?usp=sharing                   감사합니다.  이진욱 드림

subject: Flex_HU: newly arrived AOI vision pc factory defected
description_text:
Dear Support team,
Flex ordered the vision pc for their AOI about 3 weeks ago because the original pc was defected in the machine.
Finally the new pc arrived so we went there to replace the vision pc on Friday. a coup
Unfortunatelly the new pc looks like factory faulty.
It won't start at all.
We can not reach the BIOS as well.
After a couple of restarts it started once, but after 2 minutes the system just freezed out and black screen again.
The local IT took the pc and run some diagnostics and it looks like the mother board is died.
The customer really pissed off as they had to wait more than 3 weeks for a new pc, and they received a defected pc.
Do you have a pc in Alzenau which you can send to the customer quickly and they can send this defected unit back to you?
The issue is escalated, I think the Flex management already involved into the case as a complete production line is not working since nearly a month.
You can see the pc details in attachement.
Thanks

Best regards,
Roland Losonczi | Technical Support Manager

I’d like to remind you of the policy of camera consignment for replacement within 5 years after shipment.

Considering the number of camera failures, you can increase your consignment stocks more.

주제: KY Camera 필드 이슈 선대응을 위한 8차 카메라 입고 관련 IQC 업무 협조 문의 건.

수신 : IQC 정수희 대리님, 고두식 차장님

발신 : MQA 고승렬 과장



안녕하십니까? MQA 고승렬 입니다.



필드 세로줄 이슈 관련 민감한 고객사 선대응을 위한 KY Vision Sensor 8차 (Case 변경 품) 30set가 금일부터 업체 기능 검사하여 명일부터 Daily로 나누어 입고 예정입니다.



현재 IQC 에서 카메라 입고 시 샘플링으로 검사 진행해 주시는 것으로 알고 있습니다.

(Power On/Off 검사 및 CXP 4CH Aging 검사에 많은 시간이 소요되어 샘플링 검사 진행)



금번 8차 30셋트에 대해서는 민감한 고객에 대한 대응 목적으로 제작된 제품이기 때문에



물론 협력업체는 전수검사로 Full Test 진행하지만, 한번 더 Screen 한다는 개념으로 30set에 대해서만 전수 검사 진행 하는 것이 어떨까 의견 드립니다.



대신, Power On/Off 및 CXP 4CH Aging을 업체와 동일하게 진행하면 검사 시간이 필요 이상으로 오래 진행 됩니다.



하여, 기타 검사 기능은 그대로 진행하되, Power On/Off 검사 횟수를 10회로 / CXP 4CH Aging 시간을 10분으로 변경하여 검사 진행하였으면 합니다.

(이미 제조 업체에서 Power On/Off 500회 및 CXP 4CH Aging 1시간 진행 및 Pass 된 제품임)



상기 내용 관련하여 의견 부탁 드리겠습니다.



감사합니다.

Subject: KY Camera 필드이슈 및 센서 ball-lift 원인분석, 대책 현황 공유



성정규부장님, 김원태차장님,
안녕하세요?





KY Camera 필드불량 문제와 관련하여 공유 드립니다.



지난주까지 총 9건이 발생되었는데요, 원인확인을 통하여

-       3건은 정상

-       4건은 센서 불량 -> 3건 ball lift, 1건 센서 자체 불량(외형적으로 ball lift가 확인되지는 않지만 Ball lift 의심)

-       2건은 센서 조립불량

이렇게 확인이 되었습니다.



그리고, 어제 오늘 삼성VD 멕시코에서 추가로 2건이 확인되었는데, 현상으로 보면 ball lift 일 가능성이 높은 것으로 추정이 됩니다.

최대한 따른 시일내에 회수될 수 있도록 부탁드리겠습니다.



그리고, Ball lift 와 관련 AMS 원인분석 보고서가 입수되어 첨부파일로 전달 드리 오니 참고하시기 바랍니다.

내용을 간단히 말씀드리면, 센서 전면부 window glass를 고정하기 위한 attach glue 도포 공정에서 발생된 불소/탄소/수분 오염이 근본 원인이고,

18년 49주, 19년 02주 생산 lot에서 문제가 발생되었고, 총 600개 생산 중 6개 정도 불량이 확인되었고, 이중에서 고영에서 3개가 확인된 상태입니다.

(어제, 오늘 삼성VD 멕시코에서 교체된 카메라도 모두 19년 02주 lot)



두 lot에서 고영에 납품된 물량이 총 100개 정도 되는데요(아래 AMS 메일 내용 기입된 수량은 틀린 내용임을 확인하였습니다.

일단 지난 회의 중에 두 lot으로 당사에 납품된 100개는 전량 교환해 달라고 요청을 하였는데, AMS 본사에 전달하고 검토해 보겠다고 한 상태입니다.

관련하여 두 lot에서 납품되어 사용된 이력을 아래와 같이 추정하고 있는데요,

[cid:image010.png@01D93ADD.331D9360]

[cid:image011.png@01D93ADD.331D9360]

그리고, 지난 회의 중 말씀드린 30개 생산 일정은

-       7/28일:  조립완료,

-       7/29~8/1일: 이엠넥스 휴가

-       8/2일부터 출하검사 후 납품 시작

와 같이 진행될 예정입니다.

30개 납품완료는 8/5일까지 가능할 것 같습니다.

분석 해 주신 결과 잘 받았습니다.



결론적으로,

1.    이슈 Sensor의 모든 Wire Pull Test 및 Ball Shear 검증을 하였고, 일부 Point에서 Fail 발생.

2.    이슈 Sensor Pin 위치 SEM – EDX 결과 Fluorine 검출 (Sensor 2ea 모두 동일)

3.    해당 근본 원인 및 해결책 수립 예정



이렇게 압축 될 것으로 보입니다.



기존 Ball Lift 이슈 발생 시 Wafer에서 불소세정을 적용하며 잔여 Fluorine을 제거하기 위하여 Argon 세정을 적용 하였고 해당 센서는 기 적용된 Lot로 알고 있습니다.

헌데 아직 잔여 Fluorine이 있고 이 부분이 원인으로 추정하고 있는 부분이 조금 의아하긴 합니다.



해당 원인 분석으로 저희와 협의 할 수 있는 내용이 있는지 문의 드립니다.



일단 제가 문의 드릴 수 있는 사항은 하기 정도 일 것으로 보입니다.



하기 내용에 대해 답변이 가능하시다면 내방 협의가 가능 할 것으로 보입니다.



내부적으로 확인 요청 드리겠습니다.

Q1. Per our data base or our tracking list, customer wants to know the failure rate per improvement actions. For example, the return or RMA rate for 1st improvement lots, and 2nd improvements lots, and third improvements lots.



Answer:

>  Based from the RMA received starting year 2018 - 2020 we have a total of 44 RMA cases related to loose bond wire (LBW).

•       Corrective action 1: Implemented CW50/2017 starting from serial ID F501701 onwards.

•       No RMA case reported after implementation of corrective action 1.

•       Corrective action 2: Implemented 2018-Mar-14 at foundry starting wafer lot: T730206.1 and assembly lot F221808.

•       No RMA case reported after implementation of corrective action 2.

>  One case for this year, RMA21-L051 coming from customer MULTIWAVE end customer KOH YOUNG TECHNOLOGY, INC.

•       RMA21-L051 is the 1st RMA case reported with sensors build after the implementation of the corrective actions 1 and 2.

•       Affected serial # F4918030158 and F0219020103.
