Importance: High



수신 : 멀티웨이브 진대현 부사장님, AMS 정상용 부장님

발신 : 고영테크놀러지 고승렬 대리



안녕하십니까? 고영테크놀러지 고승렬 입니다.



CMV12000 Sensor Ball Lift 관련 이전 이력 검토 중 확인된 추가 사항 공유 드립니다.



지난 2018년 12월 11일 AMS Report에는 3종의 개선 방안이 있으며



2종의 개선방안은 해당 이슈 전 적용이 되었을 것으로 보입니다. (실제 적용 완료 된 제품 맞는지 확인 요청 드립니다.)



그중 제일 마지막 Halogen이 포함된 Glue 영향이 있다고 판단, Glue를 변경 하는 대책이 있었으며,



이는 2019년 5월 15일 Process 적용 예정으로 회신 받았습니다. (2019년 5월 15일 Process 적용 되었는지 확인 요청 드립니다.)



이슈 발생한 Sensor는 2018년 49주차 및 2019년 02주차 생산으로 해당 Process가 미적용 되었을 것으로 판단 됩니다.



3번째 개선 방안 미적용으로 인하여 Ball lift가 발생 가능성이 있는지 확인 요청 드리며



현재 저희 납품 완료된 Sensor Lot 중 3번째 방안까지 최종 적용 완료된 제품과 그렇지 않은 제품의 수량 확인 요청 드립니다.



위 내용으로 차주 화요일 논의 진행이 되어야 할 것으로 보입니다.



문의사항 회신 요청 드립니다.

subject: Problema con review
description_text:
Buen dia Team Khoyung

Tenemos un problema con una review, el cual al abrir la aplicacion se queda totalmente trabada, validamos los siguientes puntos:


1-      Se intala otra version y sigue con el mismo problema

2-      Se realiza detach a la ultima semana por si hubiese algun problema con los datos, se genera una nueva BD pero el problema aun persiste.

3-      Se reinicia aun asi sigue el problema

4-      Se apagan los equipos tanto AOI como Review y aun genera el problema.

5-      Se deshabilita el Firewall pero aun sigue con el problema.

6-      Hay sufciente espacio tanto en el equipo como en la Review y sigue el problema.

Mando los numeros de serie del equipo y review.
AOI: AL-SL-00478
Review: AS-SL-00478R


Saludos.



Ricardo Bustos
Test Technician AOI
Plexus
Plexus Guad
Paseo del Norte #4640
Guadalajara Technology Park
Zapopan, Jalisco

subject: [Amkor K5] Offset Coordinate 설정에 따른 Offset Scatter 차트 방향 확인 요청 건
description_text: 수신 : SPI SW Front Desk 담당자님.     안녕하세요.  KYK TS팀 김경호입니다.     Amkor K5에서 SPI의 Offset Coordinate 설정에 따라 Offset Y 좌표 변경을 테스트 하던 중 문의사항이 있어서 확인 요청드립니다.  테스트 샘플은 고객이 Offset Test 를 위해 임의로 솔더 프린트 좌표 수정하여 X,Y 각 방향으로 +50um Offset을 주고 제작하였으며, SPI 에서 검사한 결과도 비슷한 틀어짐 결과를 보입니다.    고객이 Y 좌표 기준점을 좌하단으로 설정 변경하길 원해서 검사설정에서 Offset Coordinate 설정을 아래와 같이 변경하였고 결과도 변경되지만 Offset Scatter 차트 상에 Y좌표가 실제 측정 값과 반대로 표시되는 문제가 있는 것 같습니다.      Offset Scatter 차트에 표시되는 AVG Y Offset 결과가 실제 측정 값과 반대로 표기되는 듯 보입니다. (기준이 좌상 일 때 Y 측정값이 (-) 이지만 Scatter Chart 결과에는 (+) )  테스트 한 잡파일과 DB 파일 전달 드리니 확인 부탁 드리고 추가로 필요한 데이터가 있으시면 회시주시기 바랍니다.  Offset Test.zip   감사합니다.

description_text: Dears,  we need our support for better optimize the board of the customer in object.  the goal of the customer is to understand what KY machine could reach the cycle time of 24 sec. In the pictures you will see the little "forks" we do not need to inspect them.  if you want to jump in today, below the TV:  1 430 795 862  3sqmykq8     after that I could ask the customer to wait for an answer one mor month and send the board in KYE.  But I can ask it if you think that we could reach at least 30/35 with the test of connectors. becvause without connectors our cycle time is less than 20 sec.  Now i'm using a Zenith 2 machine (8M-15um) without use DLP, due to reduce cycle time     thanks for your support  All the best  Lucio

subject: [밸류플러스] SPI Bad Mark Teaching tool 이슈 확인 요청 건
description_text: 수신 : SPI Vision Front Desk 담당자님.  참조 : SPI SW Front Desk 담당자님.     안녕하세요.  KYK TS팀 김경호입니다.     밸류플러스에서 신규 Bad Mark Teaching Tool 사용을 위해 버전 업데이트 후 확인 시 등록한 Bad Mark 를 Test 했을 때 카메라 위치가  티칭한 위치가 아닌 다른 곳에서 검사가 진행되는 문제가 있습니다.   업데이트 버전 정보    Bad Mark Teaching 위치   Bad Mark Test 시 카메라 위치    테스트 시 카메라 위치가 처음 티칭한 위치가 아닌 곳에서 테스트를 진행하는 문제이고, 조명 설정을 바꿔서 여러번 위치를 맞추고 다시 티칭을 하였으나 현상은 동일하였습니다.  추가로 Ceditor에서 확인 한 어레이 간 간격과 배드마크 리스트에 있는 어레이 간격이 다릅니다.  Ceditor에서 확인한  X 간격은 아래 이미지와 같은데, Bad Mark 리스트에서의 간격은 X가 108.1 입니다. 대략 10mm 정도 차이가 있습니다.  Use Same Position for all Panels 옵션이 체크되어 있음에도 간격이 다른 이유도 확인 부탁 드립니다.   문제가 발생한 잡파일 및 시뮬데이터를 아래 링크로 전달 드리니 확인 부탁 드립니다. ValuePlus_240111.zip      이상입니다.

subject: data backup using MES
description_text:
Hello Helpdesk,

               We got a request from our customer Siix. This is for the retention of production data from KY AOI machines and export automatically to customer's assigned server. The process is to use MES/BRM for exporting data. The data requires are details of inspection result for each PCB (good, NG and Pass) in csv file also the data images of all no-good result. According to Siix the said request application is currently use to Siix Hungary and they want to use it same format. Please advise if we can get the current kbr files use by Siix Hungary and share to us. If there's a require cost for the said request, please inform us. Thank you and hoping for your immediate advice.


Best regards,

Al Soriano
Asst. Service Mngr.
Fuji Philippines Corp.

subject: Cotización de ram
description_text:
Buen día team.

Me podrían apoyar con una cotización de memoria ram para el siguiente equipo por favor para dejarlo de 64 GB. SS-SL-05234

Y otra cotización por RING BELT #Z951014-000047 por favor.

Quedo en espera de sus comentarios.

Best regards
Cristian Antonio Espinoza Cardenas.
Process Engineer.

subject: KSmart OCR Capabilities
description_text:
Good afternoon,

I’m an engineer at a circuit board assembly facility. We have various Kohyoung products including the Zenith 2. We use the KSmart Solutions software to take images and evaluate various processes.

I know that KSmart Solutions has Optical Character Recognition capability, but I’m told that it is not really OCR and that you must tell the software what characters to look for. It will compare to the characters it recognizes and give a pass/fail output.

Does KSmart Solutions have the ability to read characters and printout the character string? Currently we manually record printed text such as serial numbers, batch numbers, and date codes on printed circuit boards. We are needing to automate the process via software. Since we already take images with KohYoung AOI machines and software, I was hoping KohYoung already has a solution for this.

subject: KSMART Server question
description_text:
Hi KYA support team,

This Monday we experienced an unusual issue with our KSMART server which is connected to 4 AOI + 4 SPI machines, and 2 OLPs.
The issue was we were unable to log in to KSMART and the GUI.
Even though every machine had network access to the server, all login attempts failed authentication, even with the kyadmin user.

We connected a monitor and mouse/kb to the KSMART server, but we were also unable to log in through the server itself.
After some time and several reboots of the server, the login authentication began working again.

We are wondering if you have any experience with this issue and if there is any way that we can prevent it from re-occurring.
Also, how can recover the KSMART server from our USB backup should there be a issue that makes it unable to function properly?

subject: Zenith CBI problems at Allegro in Sydney
description_text:
Dear Jeff     Please find below the issue at Allegro in Sydney. The one Edwin sent you an email recently.  Zenith s/n: AL-SL-00885  Software Ver 2.7.5.0_H02     As per Whatapp yesterday at Allegro we are have a lot of
difficulty programming ‘Lead Foreign Material’ on all components except chips,
we could not find how to mask the body so it would keep detecting the body and
result in a NG, as a backdoor work around we set a height mask based on the
body height.     Please find below OneDrive link to 3 CBIs     Allegro Files      1st CBI is failing ‘Lead Foreign Material’ even
with the height mask, we would like to turn off the heigh mask set a mask of
distance from the body like in ‘Lead Bridge’.  2nd CBI What is the best way to do this sort of
component (more the horse shoe shape lead then it being a LED), Body detection
is reliable but have two ideas on this  
 
 Set body detection to
     just the centre tan colour section, then pull the lead to the centre point
     of the horse shoe shape. Benefit Solder fillet is on the outside. Downside
     some body inspections are outside the body (co-planarity, polarity).  
 Set the body like a
     chip. Benefit body inspections are inside the body (co-planarity,
     polarity). Downside the Solder fillet is inside the body.   3rd CBI Is a tricky shape can the body detection
be done with settings (currently it does not follow the angle) or do we have to
go to Odd shape and manually teach it?        Allegro also want to know what they can do on the (white
dot) polarity for the 2nd CBI, they say the mark can be covered by
the solder wetting.          I could not see any feature in the tan coloured section so
for me if both ends are covered in solder wetting then there is no feature
left.  But if one end is not covered then we should be able to. If
it is the marked end is uncovered we should be able to detect the mark, if the
non-marked end is uncovered then could we check for the absents of the mark?        Kind Regards  Beat Codoni

subject: (주)피제이전자 김동훈 대리 입니다. (*SPI 장비 보드검사 SPC Data 저장 않됨 Critical 문제발생 긴급 개선 요청의 件)
description_text:
안녕하세요 (주)피제이전자 김동훈 대리 입니다.


SPI 장비 보드검사 SPC Data 저장 않됨 Critical 문제발생 개선 요청드립니다.

1. 문제 현상

 ⓐ 장비 보드검사하여 지속적으로 작동 됨

 ⓑ 장비 SPC 분석을 위해 MACHIN SPC 실행 보드리스트 당일 조회시 아무 투입이력 없음 (GOOD/PASS/NG 전부) 11월03일 오후 16시 30분경

 ⓒ 과거 이력조회 22년 10월 이전 보드 LIST 전부 조회 투입이력 보이지 않음

 ⓓ 장비 PC Data 파일 이상으로 추정 폴더 확인시 타 동일 설비와 다르게  하기 사진과 같이 "202211.ldb" 파일이 한개더 있음 확인

 ⓔ Data 변환시점으로 보여 장비 가동 정지 후 5분 동안 대기시 파일 동일한 상태임

 ⓕ 장비 전원 Reset 후 SPC 실행 보드 이력 조회시 동일하게 보이지 않음

 ⓖ Data 폴더 상태 확인시 "202211.ldb" 사라짐

 ⓗ 장비 검사가동 보드검사 완료된 시점의 SPC 조회 보드 투입이력 보임

 ⓘ SPC 22년 10월 31일 이전 보드 투입 이력 조회됨 확인

 ⓙ 22년 11월 3일 16시 30분 --> 11월 01일 보드 투입이력 없음 확인


[cid:278f9392a0e9e10f01a9feece1438fca.png]

Data 가 유실되는되도 불구하고 장비가 지속 가동되었다는게 더 이해가 않됩니다.

Data 저장관련 Check 등 문제점에 대한 상세사유 회신 요청과 긴급 개선 대응 부탁드립니다.

subject: [삼성전기] MFC SMT line 증설관련 견적문의 (AOI)
description_text:
수신 : 고영 박진태 과장님 
 
발신 : 삼성전기 조범준프로 
 
 
안녕하세요. 
 
현재 부산사업장 MFC라인에서 SMT line으로 양산 운용 중인데, 증설이 필요하여 연락드립니다. 
 
SMT line 1set를 증설하는데, 귀사의 S-AOI와 P-AOI에 대해서 견적서를 요청드리고자 합니다. 
 
이번 주 투자심의회에 상정이 필요한데, 죄송하지만 수요일 저녁까지 송부 가능하실까요? 
 
우선 심의회를 위해 기존 제작된 것과 동일 사양/수량으로 견적서를 긴급 요청드리고, 세부 사양 및 견적 수정은 다시 진행할 예정입니다. 
 
단, 칩 사이즈가 3225→5750으로 증가하고, leadframe 외곽사이즈 및 CP(Carrier plate) size는 동일합니다. (1 frame 내의 chip 수가 40→25개로 감소) 
 
답장 부탁드립니다. 
 
감사합니다.

subject: Etiqueta Unica Por Panel AOI (Proceso Magazine Unloader)
description_text:
Buenas Tardes

Espero se encuentren bien

En la actualidad estamos implementando un nuevo proyecto AOI consolidación el cual consiste en colocar Magazines Unloader. Y que tengamos a la salida del proceso Unidades con falla y unidades sin falla

No aviamos tenido problemas con el tema de reparación ya que todos los modelos con lo que contamos en otras líneas si cuentan con Etiqueta y escaneando la tablilla obteneos información de la falla (exactamente la tablilla)

El problema fue cuando implementamos una línea la cual no cuanta con etiquetas y no es posible obtener la información por tablilla.

La pregunta es si con una etiqueta por panel podríamos casar el enumero de serie con cada una de las tablillas

Por ejemplo si colocamos una etiqueta por Arreglo sería posible asignarle el mismo número de serie a cada tablilla y así poder visualizar el registro en las bases de datos

[cid:image001.png@01DA4946.2DEB61B0]

Saludos !!

JT

subject: Review Station Setting
description_text:
Good morning,

What is the setting that needs to be active to scan a PCBA after it has been classified to see both top and bottom records in the PCB list? Currently when we have a job that has two sides, once the first side has been classified at the Review Station, when the PCBA is scanned again for the second side to classify, the first side record is not appearing in the PCB list.

This is not preventing us from production, but in the past we have been able to see both or all records for a PCBA. We like to rescan PCBAs that have returned from our Repair team to cross reference with our Production software to ensure the correct defect was repaired. Again, now we are only seeing one record and that record appears to be the most recent. We would like to be able to scan a PCBA and see all records associated the PCBA in the PCB list. I have gone through the Review Set Up and cannot find the correct setting.

Thank you,

Aaron J Lafond "aj"
Manufacturing Technician III
Enercon Technologies
39 Northbrook Dr.
Gray, Maine 04039
207-657-7000
480-205-5160

subject: [Denso]특정 잡파일에서 FOV옵티마이즈 이상 발생 건
description_text: 배경 및 내용  고객사에서 작성한 특정 잡파일에서 하기와 같이 FOV 옵티마이저가 이상 동작하는 것으로 확인이 되었습니다.  아랫쪽 어레이에 대해서만, DummyFOV가 작성이 되고 있습니다.  해당 현상이 원인으로 작용하는지, SPIGUI로 잡로딩시마다 FOV옵티마이즈가 신규로 발생하여, CEditor에서 지정한 FOV Margin 등의 정보가 반영되지 않은 FOV옵티마이즈 및 자동검사가 되고 있습니다.  EPM에서 새롭게 작성하여도 현상이 개선되지 않으며, Dummy FOV가 작성된 영역이, Dummy가 아니라 육안으로 확인이 어려운 Pad가 작성이 되었을까 확대/확인을 하여도 Pad가 있는 것으로 보여지지 않습니다.    관련하여, "KY_SPI_Setup_x64_5.1.0.0_T03_0b56111709_0119"으로 확인하여도 이슈가 개선이 되지 않습니다.        문제가 발생하는 잡파일은 하기의 링크로 첨부 드립니다.  https://help.kohyoung.com/helpdesk/attachments/47267429255

subject: Documentacion de proveedor para acceso a Visteon
description_text:
Hola Felipe:
Por el cambio de año necesitamos completar su expediente de contratistas, favor de atender lo siguiente:

Para todos los FSE’s que puedan venir el resto del año necesitamos (si algún otro ing. Se los pido me dicen para verificar):

-              Constancia del SUA y comprobante de pago/deposito.
-              Copia de INE de cada FSE que pudiera acudir.

Estoy agregando un paquete de documentos que deben ser llenados de la siguiente forma:
1.            Carta informativa CTPAT para proveedores: Llenar los datos, nombre y firma del representante.
2.            Carta responsive: Agregar membrete de XXXXXXX en el área designada, Llenar los datos, nombre y firma del representante.
3.            Expediente para contratista: Llenar los datos considerando que el periodo del trabajo será de la fecha de llenado al 15 de Enero del 2024 para tener cobertura el resto del año.
4.            F-GEN-EHS-006A Política de Seguridad Salud y Medio Ambiente: Llenar y firmar datos del representante y además cada FSE debe leer y firmar al costado de cada hoja para que conste que a leído la política.
5.            F-GEN-EHS-006G Lista de personal de contratista: Llenar lista de los FSEs que pueden ser asignados a un servicio aquí en Visteon.
6.            Política de ética: Leer y llenar datos de representante, además cada FSE debe leerlo y firmarlo en alguno de los costados.
7.            Principales reglas de Seguridad 2024: Leer y llenar datos de representante, además cada FSE debe leerlo y firmarlo en alguno de los costados.

Favor de completarlos a la brevedad  y regresarlos por este medio.


Best Regards!

Hello Nabil,

We have 2 different Jabil projects.

One of them is almost finished, I just need a little help about 3D measurement.
Could you connect to the machine tomorrow?

On the other hand we have a glue inspection project.

They need to measure the glue next to the high component, because if the glue is not connected tot he component it means a defect.
They also need to inspect the ring sas restricted area.
The glue is not UV resistive.
The glue height is between 2-3.5 mm.

What is the best solution for measure this type of glue?
Is it possible with Neptune or another KY machine?

Where can I check the Demo machine Axial Resolution? Because if its 5um then I can inspect max 1.5mm thick materials.

The Jabil engineer said the Parmi AOI capable to measure this type of defects but he want to buy Koh Young machine.
Interested any solution by KY. AOI,Neptune, etc.

Pictures about the glue.

subject: BBT
description_text: 안녕하세요.     BBT 오작동 관련 문의드립니다.     BBT Multi Vendor Teaching 관련하여 몇몇 MDB Job 파일에 여러개 Vendor를 등록하여 사용중인데     생산 중 확인해보니 등록된 Vendor 정보를 정확하게 읽어들이지 못하고  다른 Vendor의 BBT정보로 검사진행되어  불량이 발생되고 있습니다.     해당 문제점 관련 조치할 수 있는 내용을 회신부탁드립니다.     □ 문제점    1. SPI Multi Vendor Teaching BBT시 A, B Vendor를 등록해두었으나 A Vendor 검사시 B Vendor 정보를 기반으로 검사하여 가성불량 발생됨   2. 추가로 BBT를 저장해 두었으나 GUI Run시 BBT - RUN이 아닌 일반 RUN으로 표기되어 BBT 정보 없이 검사되는것으로 보임

보낸 날짜 : 2023-12-30 22:10:48







제목 : RE: Re:Re:버블 가성불량 개선 요청의 件.






정종백 부장님 안녕하세요 고영 이진욱 입니다.

1차로 보내주신 버블 가성불량 케이스에 대한 자재에 대해 시뮬레이션 데이터 학습을 요청 및 진행해 볼 계획입니다. 이에 대한 내용을 전달 드립니다.

현재 두가지 문제가 있는데요


1.  가성불량 케이스로만 신규버블엔진 학습을 진행 해 본 케이스가 없음

·         보통은 실제 불량 케이스를 기준으로 학습합니다. 그래서 유관부서의 피드백을 통해 개발가능여부를 1차 검토 예정입니다.

·         상기의 케이스로만 개발 불가 시에는 차후 실제 불량 케이스들을 모아서 2차 학습을 진행 해야 합니다.


2.  본사 설비에서는 여러 개의 버블을 하나의 버블로 디텍되는 사례가 발견되지 않음

·         해당 사례의 기준으로 시뮬레이션 데이터를 취득했기 때문에 이 또한 유관부서의 검증이 필요합니다.

·         현보에 있는 설비에서도 현재 시중에 나와있는 버블엔진을 채택해서 사용 시에 문제가 없을 지에 대한 검증이 필요합니다.

·         개인적인 의견으로는 현보 설비에서 사용하는 버블 엔진이 적합하지 못하고, 첨부의 신규 엔진 적용에도 현상이 동일하다면 버블을 디텍할 때의 UV 조명 밝기가 상대적으로 낮아서 그럴 수도 있다고 예상 됩니다.

·         하기의 매뉴얼 대로 하면 자체적인 적용은 쉬운 편 입니다. 서비스 대응이 필요 하시다면 요청 부탁드립니다, 만약 저의 부재나 현장 미방문에 의한 헬프데스크를 통한 원격시엔 적용후의 장기 모니터링은 불가 하다는 부분 사전 전달 드립니다.



1.   버블엔진을 변경하기

•   유첨의 Model 4d updates 다운받아 설비로 이동하기

•   C:\KohYoung\OCT\OIThicknessMeasurement\OIPredictor\Inspection2d\Bubble\ReClassifier 안에 파일을 넣기

•   [cid:image001.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]

•   C:\KohYoung\CCI\Vision 의 VisionConfig2.json 파일을 Notepad++ 로 열기

•   [cid:image002.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]

•   하기 경로의 파일명을 model4d 로 바꾸기

•   [cid:image003.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]

•   GUI 재실행 하기 (필수)

2.   버블 엔진 변경으로도 현상이 동일하다면 잡파일의 UV 검사 밝기를 약간 올려보기

•   현재 검증이 필요한 JOB파일에 우측버튼을 눌러 EDIT WITH NOTEPAD++ 로 엽니다 (사전에 잡파일을 백업합니다.)

•   [cid:image004.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]

•    UV VALUE=20 을 36 으로 변경 합니다.

•   [cid:image005.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]

•   이후 잡파일을 다시 불러오기 하여 가성불량 케이스가 개선 되는 지 확인 (필수)



감사합니다.

Subject: RE: Re:Re:버블 가성불량 개선 요청의 件.

수신 : 정종백 부장님

부장님 안녕하세요 유선상 말씀하신 검사원리에 대해 간단한 도식으로 그려 추가첨부하여 회신 드립니다.

부품 상면과 코팅 경계에서 반사되어 들어오는 레이저 빛을 통해서 각 경계영역을 그려 사이의 범위를 계산하는 방식입니다.

Cc: '백지명' <bjm@hyunbo.com<mailto:bjm@hyunbo.com>>; '민진기' <mjk@hyunbo.com<mailto:mjk@hyunbo.com>>; '이민재' <mjlee@hyunbo.com<mailto:mjlee@hyunbo.com>>; 국내총괄 <kyk@kohyoung.com<mailto:kyk@kohyoung.com>>; 한경진 _ kyung jin Han <jinny.han@kohyoung.com<mailto:jinny.han@kohyoung.com>>
Subject: RE: Re:Re:버블 가성불량 개선 요청의 件.

수신 : 현보 정종백 부장님

안녕하세요 고영 기술지원팀 이진욱 입니다.

두께 검사 원리는 유첨의 자료 확인 부탁드리며

좀 더 정확한 설명을 드리면, Neptune 의 두께 검사 방식은 NIR (근적외선) 레이저를 이용한 분광법으로 유기체를 확인하는데 유용한 방법 입니다.
근적외선은 가시광선보다 약간 파장이 긴 대역으로 유체를 투과하는데 좀 더 유리한 파장대의 영역 입니다.
각 유체는 고유의 굴절률을 갖고 있는데, 굴절률이란 주어진 소재 내에서 빛의 속도 대비 진공 상태에서의 빛의 속도의 비율로 정의 합니다.
공기의 굴절률은 1로 정의하는데 즉, 다른 유체들은 1보다 크다는 의미가 되며 1보다 크다는 의미는 빛의 속도가 감소한다는 의미이고
빛의 속도가 감소한다는 것은 파장으로 움직이는 빛의 위상에 변화가 생긴다는 뜻입니다.

코팅액 표면에서 반사되는 빛과 , 부품 상면에서 반사되는 빛.  즉, 대상체 간에 위상차가 발생 하면서
특정한 위상에서는 보강간섭(max 한파장) 이 발생하여 밝게 보일 것이고 또 다른 특정한 위상에선 소멸간섭(max 반파장)이 발생하여 어둡게 보일 것 입니다.
이를 저희 Camera 에 있는 Photo Sensor 가 빛의 위상차를 감지하고 밝게 보이는 부분과 어둡게 보이는 부분을 Data Processing 하여 처리하게 되면
저희 Debug image 에서 볼 수 있는 두께 상면의 영역과 코팅 상면의 영역을 확인 할 수 있게 되며 그 편차를 계산하면 두께 값을 산출 할 수 있습니다.
마이켈슨 간섭계의 원리와 유사 하오니 참고 하시면 도움이 될 것 같습니다.


[cid:image006.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]
[cid:image007.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]

Neptune 두께검사의 제약점 중 한가지는 높이 부분에서 검사영역에 제한이 있다는 부분 입니다.
Camera 가 특정 높이에서 대상체를 볼 때 갖고 있는 특성으로써 검사기가 Focusing 가능한 영역을 위나 아래로 벗어나버리면 검사영역에서 벗어나 버려 올바른 검사를 진행 할 수 없게 됩니다.
즉, 제품이 들떴을 때 0 이 나왔다가 안착을 다시 진행 한 후 검사 했을 때 양품이 나오는 현상은 지극히 설비 측면에서 자연스러운 현상이며
안착을 개선하거나, 제품이 들뜰 걸 대비하여 카메라위치를 위로 이동시켜 검사영역에 코팅 경계 영역이 들어 올 수 있게 하는 방법이 있습니다.
카메라 위치를 MCS란 모션제어시스템에서 고정으로 위치를 잡거나 다른 부품에는 제약이 있을 우려가 있을 때 특정 부품만 Probe 를 이동시켜 좀 더 높은 영역에서 경계를 찾도록 설정할 수 있습니다.
설정에 의한 추가 제약점은 특정 부품의 코팅 경계만 찾으러 Probe 를 이동 시킬 때는 대상체에서 Probe Moving 이 추가로 발생 되기 때문에 CT 가 다소 늘어나게 되며
안착이 불량할 걸 예상하고 너무 높은 영역에 MCS 세팅으로 Camera 를 두고 검사를 하게 되면, 정상 안착품이 오히려 코팅경계를 추출하기 좋은 Focusing 영역에서 벗어 날 가능성 또한 존재 합니다.

[cid:image008.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]

상기의 설명 부분이 누락된 것으로 보여 추가적으로 메일 회신 드립니다.



*추가로 일전에 요청하셨던 리뷰 바코드 정보 는 하기의 세팅을 참고하셔서 출력여부 검토 부탁드리고, 버블 사이즈 um 표기는 아직 개발 완료가 되지 않은 상황이라
추가적으로 내용 업데이트 드리도록 하겠습니다.
[cid:image009.png@01DA4E14.1211A670]







감사합니다.
이진욱 드림

description_text:

subject: [서울반도체] 잡로딩 시 VisApp Crash 발생 건
description_text: 수신 : SPI Vision Front Desk 담당자님.  참조 : SPI SW Front Desk 담당자님.     안녕하세요.  KYK TS팀 김경호과장입니다.     서울반도체 고객사에 납품 된 신규 장비 검수 과정에서 표제와 같은 이슈가 발생하여 확인 요청드립니다.  납품 된 설비는 MEISTER S+(25M3.5um & 3Layer RGB ) 이며, 아래 버전 적용 시 잡로딩 과정에서 빈번하게 VisApp Crash 가 발생하고 있습니다.    GUI에 포함 된 1.10 대 비전 버전을 설치하면 2D Top 조명 사용이 불가하고 2D 검사 이미지 배경이 빨강색 또는 노랑색으로 보이는 문제가 있어서   공지 된 출하버전에 따라 비전 버전을 1.9.6.5_r189 로 적용하였습니다.  1.9.6.5_r189 적용 후 검사에는 문제가 없으나 잡로딩 시 Crah 가 발생하고 있어서 양산 적용에 문제가 있는 상황입니다.  이슈 로그를 아래 경로로 전달 드리니 격무로 바쁘시겠지만 확인 부탁 드립니다.  서울반도체_VisApp Crash.zip      이상입니다.

subject: 고영 AOI Deploy 후 OCVR 삭제되는 문제 문의 件
description_text:
▣ 수신
 : 수신처 제위 
 
▣ 발신 : 삼성전자/SMD제조파트 김남규(☏ 010-9428-5864) 
 
 
 안녕하세요. 
 고영 AOI설비에서 OCVR 삭제되는 문제가 간헐적으로 발생하고 있어 
 아래와 같이 문의하오니 조치방법에 대해서 답변 부탁드립니다.

 OFF라인 → 양산라인 Deploy 후 1107-002905 마킹문자 OCV/R 없음으로 추가 등록 생산유실 발생

subject: zenith2 PC 재 부팅 후 GUI WORK STOP 분석 요청의 건
description_text:
안녕하세요. LS ELECTRIC 문진원입니다.
12월 27일 ZENITH2 GUI WORK STOP 이슈로 PC를 교체하였습니다.
재 부팅하면 GUI 실행 20분 이상 지나야 정상적으로 되는 문제가 발생되었고 몇 달동안 LOG 등 취합해서 보내드리고 가지고 가셨는데 해결책을 받지 못했습니다.
이에 교체된 PC를 분석하여 원인 파악 및 해결책 요청드립니다. 현재 다른 ZENITH2 2대가 동일한 현상이 발생되고 있으니 PC 분석하여 해결 방안 요청드립니다.
1월2일 저녁에 박종현사원편으로 PC를 보내드렸으니 2월달에는 개선될 수 있도록 부탁드립니다.
이상입니다.

안녕하세요

이씨스 품질관리팀 김영대 입니다.

평소 업무 도움주셔서 감사합니다.



BDC Pin 휨 불량관련 하기 요청사항 확인하여 회신 요청 드립니다.



ㅁ 요청사항

 1. Press Fit PCB Hole 보정 강화 ----- 이성욱 M / 이석재 CM

  - 현재 : 2hr/1회 자동보정

    └ 육안으로 틀어짐 5 이상 확인하여 5 이상 틀어짐 발생 시 재 보정 실시

       → 육안 미 확인 또는 5 이상 틀어짐 발생 시 재 보정 누락 발생 예상 됨

  - 개선요청사항

    1안) 2hr/2회 자동보정

    2안) 자동 보정 후 5 이상 틀어짐 발생 시 강제 재보정 인터락 반영



 2. PIN VISION 검사기 카메라 정밀도 점검 ----- 이성욱 M / 이석재 CM

  - 카메라 정밀도 점검 계획 수립 및 점검결과 report 접수

     └ 고영측 유선통화 결과 2~3년/1회 카메라 정밀도 점검 필요

  - 우선순위 : BDC (기존) → IBU (북미/내수)



 3. 기초질서 위반 개선대책서 ----- 품질본부



 4. Pin 휨 개선대책서 ----- 품질본부





문의사항 있으시면 메일 및 유선으로 연락주시기 바랍니다.

감사합니다.

Hello Zoltan,



The log has already been sent to R&D, and I have a few questions regarding the PC Freeze issue.

- When was the New Vision SW that was delivered updated? Around 8:40 AM?  Yes, you are right.

- After the Vision SW update, it seems that no problems occurred initially. Is that right?   There were a lot of MES setup problems that had to be solved from the machine side (by Jarous Manar). Betreff: RE: RFQ - Alps - H9 Windows 10 upgrade BOM

Hello Daniel,
Due to machine availability I only upgraded the AOI in Alps this week.
SPI is scheduled for January.

During this installation I found that the RAM modules, PN 504091-000128 have been sent of mixed types.
This was not visible until fully unwrapped for installation as they all have same part number on the packaging.
Some of RAM packages were clearly opened previously as the packaging was not standard.
While I managed to select enough of same type to get the AOI upgrade complete, this is not possible for the SPI and I need some of RAM modules replaced.
Each bank of 4 memory slots needs to contain all modules of same type (speed and manufacturer).
As you can see on the attached picture I have 8 memory cards from 4 different batches.

Ones marked Unsure and one marked OK seems same but ones marked as ‘Return’ are different speed and also one is from different manufacturer.
As a matter of test I loaded this kit in the AOI PC and – as expected – that PC would not boot.
I would need all 8 modules to be exactly same – I can send back 2 or 3 of them (or all) if you can verify your stock to match the rest.

Please advise how can we proceed with replacement.

subject: Plexus - Heavy weight option
description_text: Hello,     Plexus has a product that needs a carrier in the first part of the SMT line and they are facing issues at SPI.  Carries with PCB's are ~4 - 4.5kg and even if they tried to slow down/speed up the conveyor, it can not be transported.  They will need the heavy weight board option, does this contains also flat belts? Because at AOI they did not face this.  Is it upgradeable a C Platform equipment?  Please share with me these details!     Thank you,  Raul

description_text:

The error with RS232Controller is shown during GUI initialization and also during KYCal initialization.

Propelec S.L.

subject: Fine Tuning Mode - Offline programming AOI station
description_text:
Good morning,

               I am looking for some assistance with a feature on the offline programming AOI station - 'Fine Tuning Mode'. This feature, which I recall from some years ago, was particularly useful as it collected all False calls, 500 good parts, and all the NG parts for a specific part number. It provided us with the flexibility to adjust the tolerances, enabling the false calls to be dismissed and the NGs to be retained. I remember there was a setting in the config file, but I do not remember which one.

                Unfortunately, I am currently unable to recall the process of configuring this feature on the offline programming AOI station or how to have the machines store this data. My recollection is that it was somehow related to the settings or management of the OPO and CDO.

               Thank you in advance for your assistance.


[cid:image002.png@01DA4DEF.012D27F0]

Thank you,
[cid:image001.gif@01DA4DEE.AAA05380]

subject: Assistance Needed with Koh Young Machine Setting
description_text:
Hi Koh Young Support,

I hope this email finds you well. I’m reaching out because we have been encountering some challenges with our Koh Young machine, specifically related to the green marking on components, X and Y line, and the score when teaching of polarity.

Green Marking on Components/X and Y lines on Components: The green highlights and X-Y lines on components are making it difficult for me during the teaching process. Is there a way to turn off these green marking and X-Y lines to enhance clarity?
Polarity Teaching:  I’ve had experience with another Koh Young machine where each picture during polarity teaching had an associated number, allowing for precise selection. However, on our current machine, this feature seems to be disabled. Is there a way to enable numerical scoring for each polarity picture? This enhancement would significantly improve the accuracy of our selections.

Thank you for your guidance on this matter.

Best regards,
Kai

subject: AOI and SPI Manuals
description_text: Good afternoon,     I am making documents on the AOI and SPI processes on a running line. I want to see if there is more information on the equipment, but was not able to find the manuals for these two.     For example, I want to specify what is a good air pressure to keep on the machines, what is a proper process for preventive maintenance, what to look out for when doing maintenance on the equipment, among other things.     If there are any documents that could provide help with this, I would appreciate a lot.      Thank you.

Buen día,

Se revisa equipo SPI y se detecta falla de conexión programa BRM

[cid:image016.jpg@01D9C505.7C5C1C60]

Se detecta en SPC plus que no se estaba leyendo mapas de proveedor desde las 3:00 pm

[cid:image017.jpg@01D9C505.7C5C1C60]


Se revisa misma tira leída en SPI no detecta mapas de proveedor, mientras en Alph si marca X-out en varios paquetes:

[cid:image018.png@01D9C505.7C5C1C60]


Se revisan tiras físicas, se corrobora que el equipo Fuji si realiza skip en los X-out de proveedor correctamente, mientras
Que los paquetes marcados con defecto en la SPI si realiza ensamble.

Se encuentra ensamblado completamente sin X-out:

[cid:image019.jpg@01D9C505.7C5C1C60]

Mallely se encargó ya de pedir los lotes involucrados para su revisión 100% y mapear los paquetes afectados.

  *   Se cargan programas nuevamente
  *   Se realiza conexión con éxito

Se revisan tableros físicamente después de los ajustes se encuentran skipendo correctamente.

[cid:image020.jpg@01D9C505.7C5C1C60]


Jhoan/Ernesto
El equipo trabajo con esta condición durante varias horas sin  alarmarse, ni indicar fallas

subject: Bad Mark SPI
description_text:
Buen día equipo Koh Young

En estas ultimas semanas se estuvieron haciendo pruebas con el Bad Mark, entre SPI y P&P, ya se tiene desarrollado un KBR por su parte para que la SPI genere el CSV desde hace tiempo. Durante las pruebas detectamos una necesidad nueva, el archivo CSV que se genera, se genera inmediatamente al término de la inspección, lo cual provoca que si hay falsos llamados genere de cualquier manera el CSV como NG en ese array, aunque le demos PASS.

La solicitud o duda sería la siguiente;


  *   ¿Se puede configurar de alguna manera que el CSV se genere hasta que haya una clasificación de los llamados si es que la hay? Como trabaja en AOI, hasta que se clasifican los llamados se genera el CSV (XML en el caso de AOI), y si sale GOOD pues que se genere en automático.

Quedo al pendiente...

¡Best Regards!

Jesús Quiñones Vargas
Test Engineer

description_text: Hello Everyone,  Yesterday i installed a new SPI SN: SS-SL-05832.  All works correctly but after some test with costumer we saw that read barcode but not correctly.  I attacked a picture with example, costumer use a barcode Code128 with only number example = "100048"   I tried different barcode in different position but continue to see "(10)0048".  i don't know why i tried to check settings and upgrade the software to version 5.0.0.0_H01_T16 but continue to have same issue.     Thanks fro the support

Ivan,



Here is our process flow. I need to figure out how to integrate the Koh Young output into this OR create a completely separate, yet similarly functioning stand alone application for the Koh Young output.



2D scan received -> Check laser table (build panel abstract) -> query all AOI data sources for records related to the panel -> build output data aggregation -> write to our managed data source -> retrieve results to line side application



The bolded part is where I’m going to need some direction from Koh Young. We pull ALL AOI results from Omron sources and aggregate them together, regardless of the platform. The best option would be to do the same with the Koh Young output.



My initial questions/thoughts revolve around the data itself.



  1.  Can I query the data directly from the database? I know that some Koh Young processes generate a new db/table based on a date changeover. Is this the case here? I’m hoping not.
  2.  OR do I query the inspection results via an API/RESTful API that Koh Young provides?
  3.  I need to map the Koh Young resultant data to my data aggregation platform, so know what I can retrieve is important to know how likely I can be successful in adding the output to our current AOI aggregation (comment, not question)
  4.  I’m assuming all failure detail is available, including component references, failure mode, and position references (x, y – on a cartesian coordinate system).
  5.  We’re currently building the sibling board information based on our own laser marking tables. Will you be scanning all boards in position and assigning failures to the individual serial numbers (assuming not)? If not, that’s okay, as long as I get positional data on where the failed component is on the panel (again – x, y position on the PANEL, not the board)



There are likely other questions, but I think this is a good start. My options moving forward will depend on these answers (and some others).



Kindest regards,
Larry

subject: ePM question
description_text:
Good afternoon,

We are working on a project that entails needing to inspect PCBAs after they have been through the depanel process. We have a customer that would like us to perform a Final Inspection on the PCBAs after they have returned from either wash cycle or flying probe test, both are performed outside of our facility. The PCBAs are being returned as single arrays.

The Gerber files we use, typically set the panel according to the design and usually have multiple arrays. Is it possible to separate out individual arrays from a Gerber file in ePM?  We want to build 3D printed carriers that simulate a panel, however, only to accommodate a single array. Is this possible or is our only option to use the entire Gerber file which will include all arrays?

Thank you,

Aaron J Lafond "aj"

subject: CSV Report file with problems (no change to PASS after analysis)
description_text:
Koh Young Support Team,

I need help with a software issue we are having on the SPI machines at the West Columbia site.
We need to use the files generated by the Auto Export function but the files are not updating their status when we have a false failure and we click on PASS to send the board forward.
Good example from Flex-Sorocaba (Brazil).
[cid:image002.jpg@01DA4E4D.36DEF280]
In these conditions where we confirm that the failure is false and we can send the board forward, normally the CSV file comes out with the last analysis status in its header, that is. PASS but in our case the CSV file generated after the inspection is not changing this information in the files and the machine is generating files with incorrect status (FAIL) as if it were a true failure.
Example of Export from Flex-West Columbia (US), where after analysis PASS the machine still generating CSV reports as FAIL status.
[cid:image012.jpg@01DA4E4D.36DEF280]
Could you please help me fix this in the software? I have already configured this same report on other sites in different software versions and have never had a problem with these reports.

subject: RE: Daño de monitores
description_text:
Internal

Buen dia Equipo de Koh Young
Para darle seguimiento a este problema que nuevamente se presenta, además un problema nuevo
1.- Monitor de la parte del frente se apaga y se tiene que operar la maquina por la parte de atrás este problema ya tiene tiempo y aun no se ha resuelto
2.- segundo problema que se presenta es que las aplicaciones de la maquina están muy lentas, en algunos casos marcan error al estarce ejecutando.
@Moreno Mauricio MNR UEXE1<mailto:mauricio.moreno@zf.com> tienes mas datos que agregar a los problemas que se están presentando

Subject: RE: Daño de monitores

Que tal Jesus,
Como lo revisamos, el monitor no se daño, cuando los visite ayer este se conecto y funciono con normalidad. Se ha dado seguimiento al problema cambiando la Frame Grabber, así como revisión de cables, etc. Todo esta OK. Es problema aislado en esos monitores del proveedor DELL, pero la SPI no esta dañándolos, así mismo ningún otro equipo ha dado esos síntomas.
De cualquier manera ya se realizo una requisición por un Monitor nuevo, cuando se tenga la guía te la comparto para que lo importen y nos indicas si necesitas ayuda para instalarlo.

Gracias, una disculpa por las molestias Jesus.

subject: Another Inspection to detect Solder
description_text:
Goodmorning Kohyoung Support,

We have an AOI leaks regarding with the presence of solder in the pad (see the image below)

[cid:image001.png@01DA4E9D.A2AFE780]

The barecopper inspection cannot detect this kind of defect because it's the same color with the solder.
We already detected this kind of defect we adjust the ROI in the solder fillet,
But the customer want another inspection to detect this kind of defect.

Our question Is their other inspection in solder fillet to detect this kind of defect?

Thank you
Best regards,

Oliver Salvador
AOI Engineer
Email:Oliver.Salvador@siix-global.com

subject: Issue with customerfunction/Exporting Data [Several Reviews;Hekatron]
description_text: Dear Kye,      at our Customer Hekatron we have an Issue with their Customer Specific export.     Find the Issuereport and additional Data at: https://hidrive.ionos.com/share/my0xp9xxhe     Until the End of December, everything was fine.   The Export they created for their KPI was exported automatically was where its supposed to be and their Dashboard was filled with everything they need.      Since they Started Production in 2024 its not working anymore.   AOI-Export is working but the review one is not.     in the Logs we see the "Network path not found" even if we try to write this on the Local Harddrive.   As they said they didnt change anything in their infrastructure.      So we tried this on our demosystem and the Export from Customerfunction is working and we just can´t seem to find the culprit.   It seems like the Event Review_Completed ist taking place, even though the Review of the Board.  Any Ideas on this?     Have a nice day & best regards      Natalie

Thanks
Tamas

Thank you your time last week on Productronica to discuss this urgent topic in details:

As per agreement we are looking for a 5Why report by the end of this week what we can provide to the Auditor.
Parallel we also looking for a certificate/declaration of the used tool by end of November. As we stated in case 5Why available we can extend a bit the time to this year to provide the propriate certificate.

Thanks
Tamás

Subject: RE: Koh Young machine calibration - IATF non-conformity

HI Stephan

thank you very much your feedback. We need further declaration or certificates from KohYoung: documents what was submitted by Roland was not enough for the Auditor.

Main issue now that the tool declarations what the Auditor verified including this on the report: See point #7.4
[cid:image001.png@01DA1EEA.7E6ACD00]

We checked Test report from Szombathely and Gdansk. Gdansk test report not including the #7.4 as you see above. Please check documents attached. Of course we did not share this to the Auditor.
There are tools before 2022 what is not having that on the report.

Danutek (Roland) offered that He can calibrate the system with an older tool what does not including that #7.4 statement but that can create more issues for the audit as we previously certified the machine with the W00C-1650.

What the Team is looking for is to confirm that the tool used in Szombathely comply with the ISO 17025 standards.
We need official statement/declaration to close this point.

Hope I could clear the situations.

Thanks
Tamás

Hi Stephan and Martin,

I would like to discuss this issue with you on a meeting agreed for next Tuesday at 10:30 at Productronica agreed with Martin previously. Please see the mail below from András.

In Aptiv we need urgent solution on this as this was an IATF Audit non-conformity of our site, in Szombathely. However all our sites use the same procedure/tooling leading to the same issue at the end.

From: Varga, Andras2 <andras2.varga@aptiv.com<mailto:andras2.varga@aptiv.com>>

Subject: Koh Young machine calibration - IATF non-conformity

Dear Mr. Gramlich,

I’m Andras Varga from Aptiv Szombathely, and I’m the responsible person for the calibration coordination at our site.

Unfortunately we’ve got a non-conformity on our IATF audit(held on 2023.10.16-2023.10.19) related to our Koh Young SPI annual calibration.
We’ve already contacted Danutek regarding it, however we’ve still struggling to have a solution that’s why we received your contact information.

Problem description:
The problem is that on the audit, we had to show the Koh Young calibration target’s calibration evidence, which has a note of the following:
[cid:image003.png@01DA1EEA.7E6ACD00]

As this report states, this can’t be traced back to any ISO 17025 standards, and it raised a problem on the audit regarding the calibration’s acceptability.
Therefore we need to have an understanding why this note is present on the document, and how can you guarantee the measurement system’s appropiateness.

Please propose a time frame within this week, when you ( or your colleague)  are able to join for conference call as we have to report the results back to the IATF auditor urgently.

Thanks in advance!

Best Regards

Andras Varga

subject: Blocking TLS V1.0-V1.1 from Harman Network
description_text:

Recientemente recibimos una notificación sobre una configuración de ciberseguridad que nuestro equipo esta implementando y se trata del siguiente tema

[cid:image001.png@01D7D15B.3C347960]

subject: OLP Fine Tune Images
description_text:
I am having a problem where the failed images are not showing up on our OLP when in Fine Tune mode.  I have some images, but no new images since yesterday morning.  I was able to check the KSMART server and confirm there were failures since then.

We do have a KYA engineer on site doing a machine install.  He has been working with our IT dept on installing a new machine on our network.  I don't know that it is related to any changes to the system that have been made due to the equipment install, but thought I should mention it.

Please advise.  I need the ability to review our defects and fine tune our false failures.

Thank you,

Jason Tomlinson

subject: Configuración de BRM
description_text:
** USI-Internal **

Buen día

En la versión actual que tenemos en trabajando en las AOI Zenith Alpha, del BRM, existe una opción la cual nos permite exportar un xml de las unidades que se inspeccionan.
[cid:dc27680a-8907-43db-83ee-cfd18b657717]

Necesitamos aplicar estas mismas funciones, pero a las SPI. ¿Qué tan posible es esto? ó ¿Qué se necesita para aplicar estas funciones?

Este es la pantalla del BRM en una de las SPI

[cid:f30f2467-f8f4-4dfe-a8ae-16852a7813f5]

subject: Koh Young AOI CFX Output
description_text:
Hi Jim and Ivan,

I am seeing a couple of potential issues with the data being sent by the Koh Young AOI machines on the SolarEdge lines.  Can you look into these or provide some feedback?


  *   I don’t see that ALP-SL-00004 (the first AOI machine on the line 1A) is sending any information at all.  Is the CFX option enabled?  Does something need to be started/restarted on the machine?


·         The second machine on line 1A (ALP-SL-00005) sometimes populates the PrimaryIdentifer field and sometimes does not, even for the same product part number.  Do you have some idea of why this may be the case?  The data below is for the same panel so maybe the one with a PrimaryIdentifier is the review station…

subject: Fine-Tuning mode /TPV
description_text:
Good afternoon guys.

We have a problem of not receiving the fine tuning adjustments on the machine, since we adjusted in the fine tuning when we are going to check on the machine there was no change.

We are using the same client and GUI version on both machines.

The CDO and CBI files are being generated normally, we were able to open the component in fine tuning and we make the changes, the deploy message appears correctly and the file is also deleted normally, but when checking the component on the machine there was no change.

The pictures of versions are below in attachment.

Could you help us solve this issue.

subject: Connector Pin Assignment
description_text:
Good afternoon,

Is it possible to assign pin placements on connectors so that the defect called on the PCB translates to the same pin location as in our MES? Currently, if a connector has a defect call, the reported pin is NOT the same in our MES. For example, if a pin 1 is called on a connector, in our MES it gets reported as something other than pin 1.

Our repair team is spending too much time finding the correct pin to repair because of the difference between our MES and how the Zenith AOI is assigning pin locations. I have attached a photo with how we would like to assign the pin numbers. Our assignments are in yellow. We understand assigning pin one and using either clockwise or counterclockwise to work around the connector. Is there a way to assign using our method?

Thank you,


Aaron J Lafond "aj"
Manufacturing Technician III
Enercon Technologies
39 Northbrook Dr.
Gray, Maine 04039
207-657-7000
480-205-5160

subject: Harman: X-out board handling on SPI's
description_text:
Dear Support team,
Harman looking forward to start using the X-out pcb handlings.
That means:

  *   if a pcb has got a badmark or x-out, the SPI should send a message to the placement machine, and the placement machine not populate that circuit
  *   if a print is bad on the panel or pcb the placement machine should not populate that
  *   if the above defects happened on the bottom side, the top side of that circuit should not populate.
Does Harman using anything like this some other sites worlwide with Fuji?
Thanks

Best regards,

subject: CUSTOMER MAHLE - SPAIN //  Questions about connectivity protocols - SIEMENS IIoT
description_text:
Dear Support team,
Customer Mahle raised below question that’s new for us.
To me is just another data collection platform that needs some development from us to supply data from our ASPIs/AOIs but may there is something already developed.
Mahle wants to build for all plants……

Customer first info:

As we have spoken on the phone, here are the questions to ask to Koh-Young, we want to connect with all machines:

What kind of connectivity / data exchange options are available for your platform?
Is there direct way to connect to machine control system or it should be local PC based?

Task is to send data to SIEMENS IIoT Platform Insights Hub (prev. MindSphere).
Desired connectivity protocols are:
Standard (Desired) protocols list
S7 (Siemens)
Modbus RTU
Rockwell (Ethernet IP)
Sinumerik
OPC UA
Simatic I/O
S7+
IEC 61850
Modbus TCP IP
System
Fanuc Focas
MTConnect

Can you match any of this?
What is desired way of sending data in your case?


Thanks to review and give feedback, not super hurry.

Regards
Javier Santos

subject: Clamping mechanism delay
description_text:
Good morning,

I am a process engineer for the SMT process of the fcBGA Line, same as Tiago.

We've been having some problems with the KohYoung Prime machine, where we see some PCBs "flying", during the clamping step (will attach a video of one of the occurrences).

After investigating and analyzing the clamping mechanism, we discovered that the boat doesn't elevate at the same time/speed, which translates itself in a clamping delay (even if brief), that affects the PCBs' behavior during the clamping step. (video attached).

Could you please help us with this? Is there a parameter or something else that can be altered in order to eliminate this?

Cumprimentos/Best Regards,
Gonçalo Coelho

Process Engineer

description_text: Hello everyone,  i have a problem with the SPI SS-SL-05276,  During the normal production the machine go in Offline and winmcs shut down randomly,  I tried to check the lan cable and i tried to change the lan Port for make some test but still problem.  When the problem happen The led Run on GNET is off and for re-start  the machine is necessary shut down all and then start again, if we don't restart all winmcs continue to take error of comunication.     I attacked a photo of G-net with the machine during the problem how do you can see the led Run is disable but normally with the key on 1 position is On.     Maybe there is some problem with the Gnet? the machine is intalled some mounth ago.     Best Regards

subject: [SPI] Aspire3 SP-SL-00563, Delay during Job change over as well as after Barcode Reading
description_text: Dear JC,     Case is created with below statement.     Aptiv Braga has a problem with their systems. Only working software on their systems is 4.8.1.0.      There are two problems.     1. When barcode is read, board takes 30-40 seconds time to enter into the machine.   2. When job change over happens after barcode reading, it again takes a lot of time in conveyor homing. Plus there is no warning message for homing.     This issue is coming on all their aspire 3. If it is happening with other machine too, this has to be confirmed yet.  Even newly delivered systems are also having the same issues. After a lot of trouble shooting, it was observed that GUI software 4.8.1.0 works well with their aspire 3 systems. Earlier er installed 4.8.1.0 software and their machine started to work fine. Even yesterday on their newly delivered machine, we installed 4.8.1.0 and their machine worked fine. However, all other software created the same issue.     Please download the logs from the given below link.     gui-5-0-0-0-delay-after-reading-barcode.zip     You will see in the 1st video that ‘Operation Time’ stops after reading the barcode and this is showed at the Barcode Window. 50 seconds later transfer starts and PCB is inspected.     In the 2nd also there is a big delay when change over the program happens. No warning of 'homing' window even if rail width is changed .     The 3rd video is with version 4.8.1.0 where everything is working properly.     Thanks & Regards, Amit Kumar

subject: URGENT!!!! (ZF_CR) Inline barcode reading issue
description_text: Machine: Dual lane SPI   S/N: SS-DX-0004  Barcode scanner: Keyence SR710     Hi KYE,       I am on the customer site to try and support a case regarding a barcode reading issue on their dual-lane SPI.      The issue is that intermittently, the GUI software will come up with a pop-up window asking to re-input the barcode. However, on clicking cancel and re-inspect, the code will be read and inspection will then be normal.      However, this is causing serious downtime for the customer and is affecting their production line. I have tried to dig a bit deeper into the logs and have found something on the KSMART interface log and the MCS log (attached).     I have also attached the current settings that is configured for the scanner.      Could you please look at this and provide some feedback as to what is causing this communication between the scanner and the GUI.      As this case is very urgent and is getting highly escalated, could you please support this with high priority?      Kind regards,     Kevin Suen

subject: [KSmart] Failed to load job list after KSMart upgrade at Bury
description_text:
Dear KYE Support,

======= We need your urgent support with the below matter - currently all SPI and AOI machines are working in local mode because we're not able to use the KSmart server. =======

History:
On Friday, 18th of August, we tried to do a backup just before upgrading the KSmart server, but we failed to do so because of "Disk space too low/Not enough disk space" message after clicking "Save on a PC" button in KSmart (sorry, no screen shots available). The next day, Saturday, we deleted one DB file named "_klink_t_result_component_main[...].tokudb" which occupied 2.2 TB. I assume it contained SPC data for AOIs, but customer agreed to lose it (I have a backup of this file anyway). After deleting this file, we were able to start the backup, but it took a whole lot of time and is over 100 GB in size. It finished somewhere during the night between Saturday and Sunday. On Sunday we finally were able to upgrade KSmart. This was the original KSmart version they had:
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, Czcionka, Prostokąt  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]

I've used these versions in the below order:
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, Czcionka, Prostokąt  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, Czcionka, design  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, Czcionka, design  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, Czcionka, design  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]


We also used Client version:
[cid:image013.png@01D9D504.40D77DB0]

After all the upgrades I "sudo reboot"'ed the server. Then, on Sunday, we upgraded one line, tested it with success and decided to go with the rest of the upgrades. We were doing annual PM, calibrations and upgrades. We had 10 machines upgraded (5 SPI & 5 AOI) on Monday morning when production started. We managed to upgrade additional 6 machines (3 SPIs and 3 AOIs) on Monday before leaving to get some rest. Everything was working well till around 20:00 (still on Monday) when I got a call from the customer that they're not able to load any job file on any machine.

I TV'ed into one machine, confirmed the problem and tried rebooting the server via SSH (Putty, sudo reboot). That helped for a minute, but the problem returned eventually. Customer switched to KSmart offline mode and continued production. When looking at Client status I could see this:
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, oprogramowanie, Ikona komputerowa  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, oprogramowanie, Strona internetowa  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]

Today, after Haotian's suggestion, we upgraded KSmart to:
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, Czcionka, design  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]

But the problem remains the same.

The error message we get at AOIs is "Server not connected" in the new job opening window after starting GUI and "Loading fail :: JOB list" after clicking "Browse":
[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, oprogramowanie, komputer  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]

[Obraz zawierający tekst, zrzut ekranu, oprogramowanie, komputer  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]

It happens on ALL AOI machines. There is something similar on the SPI machines as well.

Here are all the log files we gathered: https://we.tl/t-Y3uridFlAh

We have TV enabled now but I assume we will not be able to do anything without R&Ds help as they did do A LOT of modifications to this server while they were here at Bury a few years ago.
ID: 1 616 724 620
PASS: im6r13i9

Anyways, we would like to ask you for R&Ds help as soon as possible. Would be perfect if someone could connect early in the morning (Korean morning). The problem is that the customer wants to have an IT engineer to watch what is being done. Therefore, we would like to ask you for an estimated hour at which someone from R&D could connect this night (night for us, morning for Korea). If you could ask R&D guys to give me a call an hour before connecting so I could inform the customer, it would be perfect. As soon as the customer connects, we will get new TV details which I can forward to that R&D guy. I can use WhatsApp, Kakao or e-mail - what ever is preferred.

Please advise!

Thank you very much for your support. This is really urgent.

One important thing: before doing the upgrade, everything worked well without any major problems. This is not network/firewall related as there were no changes here as far as we know.

Pozdrawiam/Best regards

---

Daniel Kotwicki
Service Engineer

subject: SPI Kohyoung - Aptiv Braga - Volume and Height issue
description_text:
Hello @sven.hoelzer@kohyoung.com<mailto:sven.hoelzer@kohyoung.com> and @kye_help@kohyoung.com<mailto:kye_help@kohyoung.com>,

I am contacting you on behalf of Aptiv Braga, I got you contact from Maintenance Engineer @Silva, Diogo<mailto:diogo.silva@aptiv.com>.

We are looking for a solution in the measurement of solder paste volume and height in SPI.

We were collecting some data from our Spi machines and noticed that for the same component we have a lot of variances in the volume and height of the solder paste. Then we decided to try to test an empty pcb(without solder paste) and noticed that some of the pads already had volume and height.
We tried to run a BBT but we can't get rid of it.

As you can see in image below and in attachment, we get a lot of false calls, majority of the false calls are in the pads that doesn't have solder mask in the sides. Is anything that we are doing wrong? Do you have another method to calibrate pads height?
I hope you can help us figure it out, otherwise we can't trust in our volume and height levels.

First step - Empty pbc before BBT (False height and volume)
[cid:image002.png@01DA0051.BE209BD0][cid:image003.png@01DA0051.BE209BD0]

Second step - Empty pcb after running BBT (Still have False volume and height)

[cid:image004.png@01DA0052.946C1340][cid:image005.png@01DA0052.946C1340]

In this image you can see,using a different scale from 0 to 50 as you can see on the right, a lot of pads already getting some height without solder paste.

[cid:image006.png@01DA0052.946C1340]

Best Regards,
David Gomes
SMT Engineering

subject: OEL : KY8030-2 Machine homing issue (error code -20)
description_text: Dear KY Team,     Customer Name:- Optiemus Electronics Limited.     Machine Model:- KY8030-2  Machine Serial Number:- SS-DL-01402     Issue- Machine was not getting home and giving error No. -20            following activity has been performed.     1. Restarted the machine and encountered the same issue.    2. Checked the power supply and discovered that the PS3 power supply was off. Subsequently, we checked the input power and found that the power supply was not coming.    3. Checked the safety relay and identified it as suspected.    4. Afterward, we replaced the safety relay with another one, ran the machine in production, and verified that it is functioning correctly.    Root cause: The safety relay was found to be faulty (NG).              Please raise the warranty for the same as soon as possible and also send the faulty part on loan basis.     your sooner response will be highly appreciated.     In case of any further query/concern, please contact me.     Thanks and Regard  Gautam singh  contact - 8448830515  mail ID - gautam.singh@nmtronics.com

Subject: Jabil: Neptune C+ project !!high priority!!

Hello Nabil,

We have 2 different Jabil projects.

One of them is almost finished, I just need a little help about 3D measurement.
Could you connect to the machine tomorrow?

On the other hand we have a glue inspection project.

They need to measure the glue next to the high component, because if the glue is not connected tot he component it means a defect.
They also need to inspect the ring sas restricted area.
The glue is not UV resistive.
The glue height is between 2-3.5 mm.

What is the best solution for measure this type of glue?
Is it possible with Neptune or another KY machine?

Where can I check the Demo machine Axial Resolution? Because if its 5um then I can inspect max 1.5mm thick materials.

The Jabil engineer said the Parmi AOI capable to measure this type of defects but he want to buy Koh Young machine.
Interested any solution by KY. AOI,Neptune, etc.

Pictures about the glue.

subject: [AOI/SC] Side camera disappearing from Device Manager from time to time at Fideltronik, AP2-SSL-00053
description_text:
Dear KYE Support,

There is a problem at one of the machines at Fideltronik (AP2-SSL-00053). This has been reported to us on 18.05.2023 but since the customer was not using Side Cameras do to lack of proper functionality, we have disabled them in AOIConfig and completely forgot about the problem. Now, after upgrading to v2.8 of AOIGUI, we turned them on again and problem returned.

Every now and then one of the cameras disappears from Windows Device Manager making KYI fail to initialize. The only solution is to disconnect it from the grabber and connect it back again. The only thing we did so far was to re-fit the grabber into its slot on computers motherboard but that didn't make any difference.

Have you ever seen this problem? I guess we need to replace some parts:

  *   Side camera
  *   Cable
  *   Grabber

Could you please provide me with proper P/Ns?

Thank you in advance.

Pozdrawiam/Best regards

description_text:
Buenas tardes MES Team

Temenos una situación crítica en Panasonic Automotive_Reynosa.
Se requiere que por medio de BRM se pueda tener control cuando la cadena del Barcode que se lea no cumpla con la longitud de cadena definido.

From: Justin Brandt <justin.brandt@nichia.com>

To: Ivan Aduna <ivan.aduna@kohyoung.com>; Daniel Perry <daniel.perry@kohyoung.com>

Subject: RE: Koh Young Demo Follow Up


Hi Ivan,



Just an update on the boards, they will now be unavailable for roughly 2 weeks starting on 8/3, so we will need to get any additional data quickly.

Will you be able to get the full data with no missing parts and the BRM tool this week?



Regards,

Justin



From: Justin Brandt
Sent: Tuesday, July 25, 2023 2:03 PM
To: Ivan Aduna <ivan.aduna@kohyoung.com>; Daniel Perry <daniel.perry@kohyoung.com>
Cc: Yoshitaka Tamura <yoshitaka.tamura@nichia.co.jp>; Andrew George <andy.george@kohyoung.com>; Mitchell Kim <mitchell.kim@kohyoung.com>
Subject: RE: Koh Young Demo Follow Up



Hi Ivan,



Yes, given all parts were present, it was definitely a false detection.

In that case, we would like to have the parts reexamined to get the full set of data with fine-tuned parameters.



We would also like to request the custom report using the BRM tool. We have the same boards used as last time available any time for testing.



Regards,

Justin



From: Ivan Aduna <ivan.aduna@kohyoung.com<mailto:ivan.aduna@kohyoung.com>>
Sent: Tuesday, July 25, 2023 12:57 PM
To: Daniel Perry <daniel.perry@kohyoung.com<mailto:daniel.perry@kohyoung.com>>; Justin Brandt <justin.brandt@nichia.com<mailto:justin.brandt@nichia.com>>
Cc: Yoshitaka Tamura <yoshitaka.tamura@nichia.co.jp<mailto:yoshitaka.tamura@nichia.co.jp>>; Andrew George <andy.george@kohyoung.com<mailto:andy.george@kohyoung.com>>; Mitchell Kim <mitchell.kim@kohyoung.com<mailto:mitchell.kim@kohyoung.com>>
Subject: Re: Koh Young Demo Follow Up



Hi Justin,



Thanks for sharing the files and thank you Daniel for the details. I think with this information I can answer some of your questions below:



  *   Data from rows 39 and 40 did not register.

     *   Why is the data missing?

This is because the components D11 and D18 were detected as "missing". And because of this reason the machine logic is designed to not run any of the other inspection conditions at this point to avoid irrelevant result data.

     *   What can be done to fix this for future measurements?

We may need to check if the components were wrongly detected as "missing". And if so, most of the time it just means that the program may need some fine tuning to be able to detect the components more accurately, so nothing to worry about.

  *   Boxes highlighted in yellow (Example Offset Y on Row #1) are measurements we would like to have revisited. The offset seems to be in the opposite direction relative to surrounding LEDs.

We may need to verify the data against the physical board, but at first glance the offset measurements look ok in the PDF report compared to the images while keeping in mind that the offset is measured from the center of the component and the origin is usually on the top left corner.

     *   Can you pull the full data from each of these LEDs with pictures included and send? If the boards are needed one more time, please advise.

Absolutely. However, we may need to create a custom report for this using our BRM tool but it's certainly possible. Let me know if you need us to create this report so we can work on it at the earliest. Also, we may need a few sample boards again to generate the reports.



[cid:image001.png@01D9BFA5.73C66070]



Best regards,

subject: FW: Case # CAS-79168-P2J5V9 - (CFX does not report defect data)
description_text:
Hi Luis,

We were having issues with Aegis not be able to record defect data in CFX communication with AOI. After a few testing and try outs, they have a request to check the bellow information. They think the problem is that review station does not provide Heartbeat.

Please review this email and let me know what we need to do, we are waiting for this to be resolved so we can move forward to CFX with all machines.

Thank you,

Michael Hojati | MES Project Lead
858-848-3969 | mhojati@hme.com<mailto:mhojati@hme.com>
[cid:image003.jpg@01D9EC5C.D8477B90]<http://www.hme.com/>
www.hme.com<http://www.hme.com/>

From: Jason Citizen <jcitizen@aiscorp.com>
Sent: Thursday, September 21, 2023 6:33 AM
To: Michael Hojati <mhojati@hme.com>
Cc: HMESupport <HMESupport@AISCorp.com>
Subject: Case # CAS-79168-P2J5V9 - (CFX does not report defect data)

Hi Mike,

We have performed additional internal tests and research with the AOI data captured in the provided CFX log from our 3rd test example yesterday working with panel barcode 'MLG30058-2A1SN87672091823'.

All test results confirmed again that the defect data appeared against that serial number using our test database and your 2023-09-08 copied database. (See Below).

So we took another look at all logs obtained during yesterday's meeting and found the review station CFX handle (KohYoung.ZENITH.APSL00147R) is not producing a heartbeat like the inspection station CFX handle (KohYoung.ZENITH.APSL00147).

If you review the logs for the 3rd test you will see there are only heartbeats for the inspection station CFX handle (KohYoung.ZENITH.APSL00147).

The next step we suggest is for you to contact Koh Young to determine why the AOI review station CFX handle (KohYoung.ZENITH.APSL00147R) is not producing a heartbeat.

As per CFX standards, the machines are supposed to send a heartbeat once every 1 to 5 minutes.
Heartbeat Class (connectedfactoryexchange.com)<https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=http-3A__www.connectedfactoryexchange.com_CFXDemo_sdk_html_T-5FCFX-5FHeartbeat.htm&d=DwMFAg&c=DSwo5WHAmQUR7kvQRzLeTQ&r=0p7A2tdU-K8sDoeotki77g&m=0_xLz4rsMlAV-q0I02ooLOY0HYEqfQxYVYdLpDW_2VsPi6s6FY__XtfTJrxKtExc&s=YVHCJlifNOS18uWn6vsApBqBwk4EWBNEVlH__-VQAhE&e=>

Please follow through with this suggestion by working with Koh Young to determine why this is happening to rule it out as being the source of the problem.

Let us know how it goes, please.
[cid:image001.png@01D9EC6E.74EBABE0]
[cid:image004.png@01D9EC6E.74EBABE0]

Best Regards,
Jason M. Citizen
US Tier II System Support Specialist

________________________________
De: Ruben Alejandro Garcia

Para: kya.support@kohyoung.com <kya.support@kohyoung.com>; Starski Hinojosa <Starski.Hinojosa@flex.com>; Gilberto Martin <gilberto.martin@flex.com>; Manuel Toledo <manuel.toledo@flex.com>; Martin Orozco Barajas <martin.orozcobarajas@flex.com>
Asunto: Idea para desarrollo para job change con QR para codigo padre

Buen día Equipo Kohyoung

Envió este correo para solicitar su apoyo para ver si nos pueden apoyar con un desarrollo especial utilizando el job change con el código padre de las unidades, esto debido a que en un equipo en especial corren unas unidades que llevan doble lado de inspección (Top y Bot), conociendo cómo funciona el job change como lo tenemos actualmente funcionando lee los barcode Hijos donde está la información del modelo y los seriales de la siguiente manera:

202354327654 800-00663 0506 1092

donde busca la siguiente información 800-00663 0506 y con ello realiza el cambio de modelo ya que el nombre coincide con el nombre del programa en la carpeta job y realiza el cambio sin problema.

pero para el requerimiento que estamos solicitando requerimos que lea el código padre que nos arroja la siguiente información.

ML800-00663-1102_TSN234000919240   esto en el lado top

ML800-00663-1102_BSN234000919240   esto en el lado bot


Con el cual se propone que busque del texto padre lo siguiente para poder realizar el cambio de modelo

800-00663-1102_T cuando este por Top
800-00663-1102_B cuando este por Bot

los programas se llaman
EPH2H-800-00663-0506_TOP
EPH2H-800-00663-0506_BOT
anexo imagen de como es el modelo y como están los barcode

[cid:e72fa26d-7089-4e81-a701-648f7d0f5cc0]

y saber si la logística siguiente podría ser correcta para el funcionamiento del Job change

pasos

  1.  lectura del QR padre y comparación para realizar el job change
  2.  después de realizar el cambio de modelo o la verificación que lea los QR hijos para la obtención de los seriales y pueda generar los XML de cada serial

Quedo a sus órdenes

saludos.............

subject: [Amkor K4] Job File Loading 불가 건
description_text: 수신 : SPI SW 데스크 담당자님  발신 : 국내 TS팀 박민우     안녕하세요 SPI SW 데스크 담당자님.  국내 TS팀 박민우 입니다.     GUI에서 Job File Loading 이 불가능 관련 에러 문의 드립니다.     배경   현 설비는 Flux 3 Layer 장착 및 Flux AI 적용되어 있음  해당 설비로 일반 Solder 도포된 제품 양산에 문제가 없는지 확인 중  Flux Pad, Solder Pad가 동시에 있는 제품도 검사가 가능해야 함    타 설비의 Job File 사용 시 Job Loading은 되나 검사 시 KYI Uninitializing 및 Visapp Disconnected 발생  Gerber 부터 새로 Job File 작성 시엔 해당 KYI, Visapp Error 발생하지 않음  12/14 신규로 Flux Pad, Solder Pad가 같이 있는 Job 작성 후 검사 시 KYI, Visapp Error 발생하지 않았으며 검사에 이상 없었음       버전   GUI : 5.0.0.0.T33  Vision : FLUX AI Vision  KYcal : 2.2.0.0  KYI : 1.2.2.4ab95325      현 증상   Gerber 부터 새로 Job File 작성 시 Error 발생하지 않는 지 확인  Job Loading 시 Load-Finished 2%에서 변하지 않으며 개체 변수 with 문의 변수 Error 발생 함      Flux 버전의 문제일까 싶어 FLUX AI Option On/Off, GUI 및 Vision 재설치 등 기타 방법으로 시도 했으나 에러 증상 동일합니다.     https://help.kohyoung.com/a/tickets/97204 의 등록된 내용대로, Flux 3 Layer 적용된 설비에서 작성한 Job은 문제가 없는 것으로 보였으나 12/27 신규로 Job   작성 후 상기 에러가 지속적으로 발생 중입니다.  금주 내 해당 에러가 개선되지 않으면 기존 1 layer로 원복 진행할 예정입니다.        에러 발생 시점  16시 46분 - Job loading 후 개체 변수, 문의 변수 Error 발생  16시 52분 - GUI 재설치 후 Job loading 후 개체 변수, 문의 변수 동일 Error 발생      레포트 파일 및 에러 발생했던 Job file 첨부드리며 추가로 필요하신 사항 있으시면 바로 전달드리도록 하겠습니다.      감사합니다.  박민우 드림.

[cid:image001.png@01DA4F78.BBE29730]

subject: [AOI] 특정 부품 검사조건 변경 적용시 적게는 30초에서 많게는 1분이상 Please wait 팝업창떠있으면서 적용 안되는 현상 문의 건.
description_text: 수신 : AOI SW Front 담당자님.  발신 : 국내TS 박진태 과장.     안녕하십니까 국내TS 박진태 입니다.     EST_대구 고객사에서 AOI 사용중 검사조건 변경하면 적용완료 되는대까지 시간이 너무 오래걸리는 현상이 있어 현장 확인 후 관련 로그 첨부드리오니   개선 방법이 있는지 확인 부탁드리겠습니다.   LOG : 2024.01.29_EST(대구) 2.8.1.1 검사조건 수정시 저장에 한참걸리는 현상.zip   증상 : 특정 부품 검사조건 수정 후 저장까지 오래 걸림.  KY_AOI_v142_setup_x64_2.8.1.1-12-g2786e20f2f    저장이 분 단위 넘어가는 부품도 있으며, 저장이 완료 안되었는지 Please wait상태에서 다른 모델 열려고 하면 두번째 메세지 팝업됨.    현장 확인시 특이사항.  담당자 인텨뷰 및 문제 파트들을 확인 해본바 파트 하나의 검사조건 파일이 19~20MB정도로 용량이 큰부품들이 위와 같은 문제가 있음.  보통 이형 부품들이며 패키지 타입은 대부분 Other이며 바디 이물검사, Oddshape_calculator 검사조건등이 들어있는 부품.  2.8.0.0에서는 please wait 팝업창이 나타나지 않아 인지는 어려우나 다른 모델 열려고 하면 메세지 발생됨  2.8.1.1에서는 Please wait 창이 저장 끝날때까지 떠있어서 오래 걸리는 것을 육안 확인 가능 함.       검사 조건 변경시마다 시간이 너무 오래 걸려 고객사에서 불만이 많은 상태이오니 확인 부탁 드리겠습니다.     감사합니다.     박진태 드림.

subject: Customer Inission Munkfors: Closed loop thete increase for some jobs ONLY
description_text: Good morning,  Description: Customer reports that closed loop theta, suddenly starts to  increase for every board on some jobs ONLY. Majority of all jobs works fine. Restarting SpiGui resolves the issue for a while and then suddenly theta starts to increase again.         Conditions: - I've verified EKRA printer origin and theta setting - Only good pads used for calculations - Only some jobs are affected (most jobs works fine) - SpiGui ver does nnot matter - Several MES versions tested, including latest on ftp KY_MES_SPI_Setup_x86_4.3.0.6584 - We also have same reports from NOKIA (MPM-printer)  Questions: - Does KYE known what is causing this closed loop theta increase issue, for some jobs only?  Best regards  Anders

[cid:image007.png@01DA34D1.A2AC48E0]

Additionally, I've noticed that while calibrating PZTs, CH1 has exceptionally random values and differs a LOT between measurements. The values which should be around 100 are jumping up and down, even when you don't make any changes and just press the CH1 button. Same happens on other channels but CH1 has the biggest differences. See this video here: https://we.tl/t-BkY6Z7dyOM

To add to all of that, I have a suspicion that something is wrong with the camera. When you zoom in a lot you can see fluctuations in the image. I assume it's the camera, because I disconnected MP-X and MP-Y connectors while looking at the live image and I could still see those fluctuations. Look at this video here: https://we.tl/t-lnsZxdY8xt

Mostly CH1 and CH3 had issues with PZT Move Error, but CH4 had it one time as well (check the log in the beginning of this e-mail). Anyways, I managed to calibrate the machine somehow, but the next day customer started reporting some problems like this:


[Obraz zawierający tekst, elektronika, zrzut ekranu, Inżynieria elektroniczna  Opis wygenerowany automatycznie]

No, the PCB is not dirty. It's a snowy image.

Next day, 21.12, we installed a new grabber card and new camera cables to upgrade this system to 12M. Everything went smoothly, but during calibrations we had the same issues as above. After starting production, we got this from time to time:
[cid:image008.jpg@01DA34D1.A2AC48E0]

We rolled back the registry changes we made, restored a backup made prior to calibrations to see if it has anything will improve, but it's getting worse.

Things I tried:

  1.  Restoring a backup made prior to calibrations - no luck.
  2.  Calibrating at different positions (having the target in the middle of the conveyor for example) - no luck.
  3.  Replacing PZT 1 and its amp, tried everything again - no luck.
  4.  Moving CH1 grating a little bit one way and the other - no difference.
  5.  Replacing IVPC boards (both) - no difference.

Now, when I tried to do the 2D light calib while weiting this e-mail I got this (see video): https://we.tl/t-PucvLmG1cr

This is why I also think something is going on with the camera or the grabber we have is faulty. We would need to put the old grabber back to check.

Anyways, I will upload all things I gathered hopefully this weekend and, in the meantime, maybe you will have some ideas about what else we can check.

My plan:

  1.  Put old grabber back.
  2.  Put old cables back.
  3.  Replace camera?

Merry Christmas and a happy New Year!

Pozdrawiam/Best regards

---

Daniel Kotwicki
Service Engineer

subject: Missing/Absent inspection
description_text:
Hi KY Team,

We are being tasked to develop a quick program to inspect only missing and absence as a final check before shipment. What is the best way to approach this?
Right now we are using the old program, saving as a new program for missing only, transferring it to a separate AOI that will be responsible for only inspecting missing and absence, but we need a way to quickly turn off all other inspections so that it will only inspect missing so that we don't have to spend time create a whole new ePMs + programs.
Is there another way besides unchecking all the checkboxes for each package as it takes too long.

Danny Nguyen

subject: Plexus - SPI Quote for measurement and readiness changes
description_text:
Hello Enrique, 
 
 
  
   
 
 Would you be able to provide a quote for fixing the readiness option and also to add volume measurments into the file export output for reference? 
 
 
  
   
 
 Regards, 
 
 
 Rene 
 
 
  
   
 
  
 
  
 From: America Support <kya_support@kohyoung.com>
 
Sent: Thursday, June 22, 2023 3:43 PM 
To: Rene Torrez <Rene.Torrez@plexus.com> 
Subject: Re: SPI Data collection
 
 
 
 
   
 



 



 
 
 
 
PLEXUS Security WARNING: This is an external email. Do not click links or open attachments unless
 you recognize the sender and know the content is safe. 
 
 
 
 
 



 



 
 
 
 
 Hi Rene,  
 
 
 
 
  
   
 
 
 
 ​Here's a summary of today's activities regarding this ticket. 
 
 
 
 
 
Readiness Function 
We tried activating and debugging it with no success. The problem turned out to be the serial number file.  
BRM is looking for a file with the name format [WorkOrder]*[Process].csv, but the naming of the available files is different. 
This format is the "new" one and the Plexus global SPI software was requested to work with only that one; AOI doesn't have this problem because it can work with both the old an new formats. 
To test the file export and while the file naming is sorted out, we disabled this feature for the time being. 
 
 
File Export 
Tested this feature and we were able to export both csv and xml files after inspection. 
 
 
Measurements 
To export measurements there are two options: 
 
 
 
 
 
Modify the current file export so measurements are added using the format you specify. This option will have an associated cost. 
 
 
Add the web service (KY Standard) functionality which has measurement export built in, this option is free of cost but requires you to support a RESTful interface with JSON messages through a
 web server. 
 
 
 
 
  
   
 
 
 
 ​I will close this ticket now as the original request for File Export has been fulfilled. 
 
 
 
 
 To continue debugging Readiness or for more information about the web service, please open another service ticket at
kya_support@kohyoung.com so we can look at each topic separately. 
 
 
 
 
  
   
 
 
 
 Kind regards, 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Enrique Garcia 
 
 
 
 
 
 MES Software Developer

subject: RE: falla en kohyoung L39
description_text:
Buen día,

Se revisa equipo SPI y se detecta falla de conexión programa BRM

[cid:image001.jpg@01D9AA4B.8555EB90]

Se detecta en SPC plus que no se estaba leyendo mapas de proveedor desde las 3:00 pm

[cid:image002.jpg@01D9AA4B.8555EB90]


Se revisa misma tira leída en SPI no detecta mapas de proveedor, mientras en Alph si marca X-out en varios paquetes:

[cid:image010.png@01D9AA49.2BDD7AD0]


Se revisan tiras físicas, se corrobora que el equipo Fuji si realiza skip en los X-out de proveedor correctamente, mientras
Que los paquetes marcados con defecto en la SPI si realiza ensamble.

Se revisa PCB 02 Lote 4417468.1 sin X-out de proveedor y marca un defecto de insuficiencia, pero al revisar PCB físico
Se encuentra ensamblado completamente sin X-out:

[cid:image003.jpg@01D9AA4B.8555EB90]

Mallely se encargó ya de pedir los lotes involucrados para su revisión 100% y mapear los paquetes afectados.


·         Se reinicia equipo completamente

·         Se cargan programas nuevamente

·         Se realiza conexión con éxito

Se revisan tableros físicamente después de los ajustes se encuentran skipendo correctamente.

[cid:image004.jpg@01D9AA4B.8555EB90]


Jhoan/Ernesto
El equipo trabajo con esta condición durante varias horas sin  alarmarse, ni indicar fallas
Me podrían ayudar a revisar por que sucede esta anomalía en los programas.

Quedo pendiente a sus comentarios,
Gracias.


Saludos!
Skyworks Solutions de México
Sheila Valdez

subject: Low Pressure Warning
description_text:
Team,

We have seen this a couple time is the last year. But we have seen 3 machines exhibit this warning in the last 24 hours.
We used to be at nominal .45 Mpa. We have been increasing it over the months to avoid low pressure errors.
I do see anything in the manual that cites upper or lower air pressure setting.

I verified the source air to be at 120 psi.

KY Line  Machine Input
Line 1    .514 Mpa
Line 4    .500 Mpa
Line 5    .603 Mpa
Line 6    .515 Mpa

We have 20 SMT machines that error is input air is less than 85 psi.

Any suggestions? I believe our house air is not the problem.

Regards,
Greg Kloiber
Sr. Manufacturing Engineer - Electronics Solutions Group
Ducommun Incorporated
2222 East Pensar Drive
Appleton, WI. 54911-8789
Tel: 920-882-7547 (office)
Tel: 920-279-3812 (Cell)

subject: Same Part with Different Package Types
description_text:
Hi,

We have a PCBA that has multiple package styles for one of the parts. One is a PowerPAK SO-8L Single and one is a PowerPAK SO-8L from Vishay. I'm wondering if it is possible to setup the AOI program so that it can recognize both package styles in 1 program. This way depending on which part we are running, we can still run one AOI program and it automatically check for one or the other.

Here are links to the product pages for both part styles, the package dimensions are in the PDFs.

https://www.vishay.com/docs/66963/sqj459ep.pdf

https://www.vishay.com/docs/73438/si7469dp.pdf

One the left is what is currently taught on the AOI, the part on the right is the one that we want to add to the same program. The one has 8 leads with the other has 5. Plus the markings on the part are somewhat different.

[cid:image001.png@01D7C982.32181710]

Let me know if anything is unclear and I'll be happy to clarify.

subject: [NSN_Chennai]_Kohyoung AOI/SPI_Query Monthly acronics backup restore
description_text:
Dear team,
       In Nokia we enabled scheduled acronis backup monthly in SPI and AOI machines.  In every month acronis backup automatically saved(7th of every month). Due to memory occupation , customer delete old acronis files. Keep last six month acronis backup only.      We tried to load last month(Dec month) acronis backup in one SPI machine by using acronis CD.  That time we face 'This is not the last volume of the back-up archive error'. Customer have acronis backup from July .(Delete old files from Jan).So we tried all month acronis backup file. We face same error.   So we suspect issue happen due to delete of old files.
  We need suggestion, if memory full what month acronis file need to delete to avoid this issue. Kindly suggest us.     Regards  Sethu

subject: [Sandisk WD] Ksmart KYSPI NG Even Process
description_text: Hi KY team,     Customer WD want to request new enhancement SPI NG event process.      1) Currently when SPI machine have NG, operator will review  false call and if result is Good machine will publish SPI APC Process data event to CAMSTAR (E3).  And if result is NG no event will be publish to E3.      2) Enhancement  - Customer proposed to have pre-event publish to E3 whenever machine have false call, before operator review.      kindly refer to the flow chart     *Ksmart BRM_setup_x86_2.6.0.41

subject: [BENCMARK] AOI TO SEND NG COMPONENT DETAIL TO PFS

subject: Mahle - Bypass in Dual Lane AOI
description_text:
Good morning

I have a question from our customer Mahle.

They have two double lane AOI in serial configuration.

The way they work is keeping one of the lanes in Bypass and the other one in inspection, in the second machine they have the opposite.

For example in AOI1 lane 1 is inspection and lane 2 bypass, and in AOI 2 lane 1 is bypass and the second is inspection.

They now how to setup a single lane in bypass, but the problem is that restaring the GUI, this configuration is lost and need to be configured again.

Is there any way to keep permanently one lane in bypass?

Thanks in advance
Best regards

José Manuel Calle
Propelec SL
